text: Left this place a bit confused. The food is just okay, basic generic texmex. I did takeout, two tacos and a burrito. When I picked up my order there was no salsa include. I asked for it, the cashier asked for $1.25 for the salsa. I asked does an order of tacos not include salsa. He said no, because the were “side orders”. Had I sat down and ordered this, salsa AND chips would have been brought to me before I even ordered. I would have been charged no extra. Do they not realize that people do reviews on them?

name: Taylor Melendez
text: I've been coming to this truck since they posted up there. The food was amazing and portion were decent. There was a man and a woman who were there in the beginning and did an amazing job. I'm not sure if they left but their replacements have decreased the experience. Food portions are lighter. Esquites came in a medium size foam cup but now come in a child size plastic cup. No more jalapenos with my order or cilantro unless you ask for it. They've gotten popular but due to their rise in popularity I feel the quality has decreased significantly. It's not the same as it was in the beginning. Food is good but quality has declined.

name: Alan Raymond
text:
I have to go middle of the road on this review. The service was prompt and courteous, but the food wasn't exactly top-notch.

I had a taco salad with shredded chicken, and it was relatively flavorful. That said, the chicken was also bit tough. The texture of the chicken degraded the overall quality of the meal.

On the upside, the salsa was spicy, fresh and flavorful...just how I like it.

This was our first trip here and perhaps it was an off night. We'll be back at some point and I'll provide and update to the review.

Cheers!

name: Peg Schoettlin
text:
I inadvertently gave a very poor review for Chapala. Actually the food and service here was excellent it was  Served hot and quickly. Server very personable.
The poor review has now rightly been posted on Mi Hacienda' s (Decatur) page.
My sincere apologies Chapala!!

name: Brandon Risko
text: Yes, this is not authentic like some of the taco trucks you will find around town, but this is a great option for your typical neighborhood "Americanized" Mexican food restaurant.  My wife and I have always had great, friendly service and the orders have always been correct.  Food is good for what it is and the salsa is excellent...lots of cilantro and onions which I love.  Also, they have great drink special during Happy Hour!  Another perk is it is within walking distance for us (especially helpful after those $10 margarita pitchers).

name: Ed Turner
text: Chapala has really improved since the new owners took over (Burrito Express , Athens) I had the Chile Verde with pork. Delicious! If you like real authentic Mexican food. You should try Chapala.

name: Emerson Oliver
text: The staff is very pleasant.  Easy to get in and out.  Not usually crowded.  The food is pretty good.  Try the specials.

name: Ronald Husa
text: We have been coming here for over 3 years and it is still our favorite restaurant. It has new management and an updated and fresh interior, new booths and tables which it did need. Some of the menu items have been updated as well and somehow the chimichanga got better!! Love this place.

name: Micheal Porter
text: Very good food, great service. Price is at least as good as comparable restaurants in the area. Lots of space if you have a large group. Oh, and they have great Mt. Dew...just sayin'.

name: Chelsy Nuby
text: My boyfriend and I have lived close to Chapala for over 3 years now and have been going there at least twice a month, sometimes more, since then. The food is fantastic with fair prices, the employees and owner are super friendly, and their specials/happy hour are great!

name: Steve Kaikkonen
text: One of my favorite places. Quiet atmosphere,  great food and great service

text: Love Chapala! This is Burrito Express (Athens) 2nd restaurant. My family is thrilled that we can eat the same fresh and quality food much closer to home! My favorites are the fajitas, Carne asade tacos, chili relleno, and California burrito! The top shelf margarita is beyond tasty!

text: Mangos is my family's go to for Mexican food in Oxford/Anniston. The food is phenomenal and the staff is like family. Love this place and can't get enough. Lots of options even for vegans.

name: Greg Lee
text: Best tamales in Alabama! Good service; it is  going to be my go to place for Mexican food. I drive past 4 places on the way there. That shounder tell ya how good it is.

name: Rachel Hamilton
text: Absolutely fantastic in all aspects. Friendly, warm and inviting staff and the food is wonderful. Cannot say enough about Miguel, his staff, and the dishes themselves.

name: Tori Barber
text: We were traveling through on I-20 and searched online for a nearby restaurant with a good rating. Mango’s Cantina and Grill did not disappoint! We were seated immediately and treated as if we were the most welcome guests in the place. The salsa, cheese dip, chips, burritos, chicken and rice, fountain drinks and margaritas were top shelf. Everything was fresh, the right temperature and very tasty!. The prices are reasonable and the service was so friendly. We hope to travel back this way in the future.

name: Erica Wright
text: Food was okay, server was nice. She got some of our orders wrong and forgot some things. (There were 9 of us) We sent two baked potatoes back because they had stuff in them that my hubby & son didn't eat nor order. They took the potatoes back to the kitchen and scraped the insides out and brought them back to the table. It was extremely obvious that was what had been done as the potatoes were torn all to pieces with the insides missing. My husband then asked for a new fresh potato and the guy that brought them out yelled " Tell your sever because I can't help you" and walked away with his hands in the air. He was very rude and that was very uncalled for. Our server returned to our table and we told her what had happened and asked for fresh potatoes. She refused to bring out new ones. Instead brought out butter and cheese for them.  I understand everywhere is short staffed and people get frustrated, but that was uncalled for. We won't be back.

name: James Poe
text: Always friendly, fast service and the prices are very reasonable. Plenty of TVs and large bar area....if that's your thing.

name: Johnnie Phillips
text: This is always a good experience. Food is hot even when I get home. Tastee to the core I recommend you give it a try. You'll say the same

name: James Robinson
text: Awful. Unbelievable what is considered "Mexican food" around here. I can make a bettter Mexican meal with canned goods and ground from the grocery store. And the beef "fajitas" are NOT beef fajitas at all. Those were tuff strips o beef with ZERO marinade, grilled to over-well done with bell peppers and onions. Disgusting. I boxed it up to bring home to my dog. Waste of money.

name: Marianne Costes
text: Great service, good food that's nicely presented, nice restaurant layout but it's pretty dark inside and I wish they had different color lights or something.

name: Natascha Lewis
text:
A hostess told the representative of our party of very good tippers that we had a 20 minute wait. An hour later, and after they seated a few ppl that pulled u after us, we were overlooked and told that we had an hour wait. The hostesses, who were very cordial to the white customers, were very short and indirect with us. My daughter in law said that they experienced the same ignorance recently when they tried to eat here. At first I thought it was because we had a party of 13, but I now know it was because we were black. Their loss though; we are some of the best tippers you will ever have because my daughter has been a server for years.

See ppl, not color.

name: Tristen
text: One of my most favorite places to eat authentic Mexican food!!! Love going to this one and the location in Lincoln. Haven't had a bad experience yet! The food is always hot, fresh, and delicious! You won't be disappointed!

name: Taquisha Garrett
text: Omg!!! First of all I came in 20 mins til closing! These were the nicest people at this restaurant an even tho it was closing time it didn’t show like most people in most restaurants!!! This is my new favorite spot.

name: Becky Smith
text: Our first time eating here. Food was ok, the problem came with our drinks. I ordered sweet tea, as did my husband. When I asked for a refill and tasted it, it tasted as though tea and coke had been mixed, so I asked for another drink. A male server comes to our table with a “tea” and a “coke” and said he brought our refills. My husband said we both had sweet tea, so he left with the coke. Another waiter comes to our table and asked if I had drank from the tea, and I said yes. Comes to find out they brought us someone else’s refill that had already been drank from. So in today’s world with COVID, they brought us someone’s else’s refills instead of bringing the pitcher to the table and refilling there. There was no discount, there was no apology and in my opinion this was a HUGE mistake. We will never eat there again, and I’ve honestly considered calling and reporting this to the health department. I understand mistakes happen, but there was no remorse for their mistake.

name: Mo
text: Meh.  Food was just okay.  Salsa tasted like sweetened, watered down ketchup...almost like Spaghetti-Os sauce.  Server was professional and attentive. Overall not impressed.  Two people eat for approximately $30 including 20% tip.

name: Jonas Sostakas
text:
This is a hidden gem!

My wife got the fajita nachos, that came on a large plate, the chips were arranged neatly. The steak was well seasoned without being over bearing. The steak was cooked to perfection, tender and juicy

I ordered the carne asada, which was excellent! It came with 3 warned tortilla shells, a side dish including shredded lettuce, pico, pickles jalapenos, and guacamole.

The salsa served with the chips was excellent, very fresh. Although it had cilantro, we asked for some more to kick it up a notch.

They have delicious ice tea, Sweet and unsweetened. They also have bottles of beer available.

I finally asked about our food and was told they forgot to put in, but offered complementary drinks. Well, our food finally came after 45 minutes, and was cold. When I asked to see a manager no one ever came, so we left! I called back and was told there was no manager there!!! What kind of business runs with no manager on a Saturday night???? Can be assured I will keep calling until I get a manager and I will NOT return. So unless you have all night to wait on food in an empty restaurant and eat cold food, I DO NOT recommend this establishment.

name: Andrew Brim
text:
EDIT 2: MORE TACOS. Mariachi has my favorite marinated pork (pastor) in town. Got 2 tacos and a Burrito Campechone (steak and chorizo). Still getting the wonderful spicy red salsa, still 5 stars.

EDIT: 2nd photo from tonight's visit. The gentleman at the window told me to try the Torta "Philly style". Got one steak, one pork. Fantastic! Still an easy 5 star.

Asked for recommendations from the kind young lady at the window.

Got steak torta (left) and 3 tacos (right, 1 each steak, pork and steak/chorizo combo).

Tried each of the 3 salsas, and loved them all. Standard red salsa was bright and spicy, Verde was nice and tangy, and the bright green (I think it was guacamole salsa) was a little creamier and more subtle.

I ate it all, with a lot of salsa. It was excellent 👏

Would definitely recommend pork or Chorizo, not because the steak was lacking, but because the marinated pork was so good and Chorizo is a personal favorite.

$17 for all in the picture. Easy 5/5

🌟 ⭐ 💫 🌟 ⭐

text: Really enjoyed the visit here! We had great service and wonderful food!! We ordered the chips and dips as our appretizer. There's three dips - bean, pico and queso. Loved all three! The chips are thin and warm! My husband ordered the birria tacos and he really loved that! He said it was the best tacos he's ever had! I ordered the steak fajitas and those were great too!! We didn't order alcoholic beverages, but we had unsweetened tea. Service was fast and she was friendly. We will definitely be back!!

resp.text: Glad you enjoyed.

Fun little addition to OWA. Welcome!

Love the building inside and out, really catches your eye.

resp.text: Glad you enjoyed.

name: Christie Davis
text: Fabulous food and wonderful server named Jennifer. She was friendly and attentive. Food was so good. Fajitas were spot on and the margaritas were some of the best I’ve ever had. Definitely will come back.

resp.text: Glad you enjoyed.

text: Really enjoyed this place!! The menu is labeled to help those with dietary restrictions and when we had a difficult time figuring out what one of our little ones with significant restrictions could have the cook came out and worked with us. Great atmosphere and the food was delicious!! The staff were all very welcoming and pleasant! Would definitely eat here again!!

resp.text: Glad you enjoyed.

text:
We've tried a variety of things from their menu. The cheesesteak tacos were a huge hit. The grilled fish (mahi) tacos were described as the best they've ever had. The Birria tacos were incredible. Portions are large.

The decor and atmosphere make this restaurant very unique and fun. Definitely our new favorite taco place. We drive from Pensacola just to eat there.

resp.text: Glad you enjoyed.

name: Allison Gates
text: I thoroughly enjoy eating at El Diablo! I come here about once a week. Jennifer is the best server! She is friendly and gets my special order right every time. The quality of the meat they use is top notch. And the seasoning is on point.

resp.text: Glad you enjoyed.

name: Kathy Prince
text: This restaurant has a unique flair.  The food is delicious, not your usual Mexican dishes.  I will be back!

resp.text: Glad you enjoyed.

name: Erika Park
text: These are wonderful people that really take care of their customers! I have a child with a lot of dietary restrictions. Their menu is very detailed with each allergen that may be in it. Example: egg, dairy, soy, gluten, vegan, vegetarian etc... This is such a relief when you have restrictions like we do. Beyond that, the chef came out to make sure that he had all of my daughters needs listed so he was sure to get it right. They were so nice and thorough beyond my expectations. And the food was delicious!

resp.text: Glad you enjoyed. Happy the work we did on the menu was beneficial.

text: Food is never fresh! Day or night; I’ve eaten there over 5 times within the past 6 months and each time I was disappointed. Fast is not cheap. The food should be severed fresh regardless of the fact of it being fast food. No one should have to pay for food that’s has been sitting under a warmer too long. Every time I have ordered a chalupa it was hard as a brick and I didn’t even feel like disputing it. The ONLY chalupa that I have eaten, “that was actually fresh”, was the chicken bacon ranch chalupa that was there for a limited amount of time and they had no choice but to make it fresh because it probably wasn’t at high demand. I’ll probably never eat there again now that I have made this post, but something needs to be done. Work ethics and training needs to be reevaluated. Workers should take pride in what they do even if it’s making fast food!

This decision will cut my visits to Taco Bell by 70%. I use to go to Taco Bell 3+ times a week. Thank god for the party pack nachos, while they last. For today my money went to Jacks :(

I can only imagine someone did not do a proper cost benefit analysis on this decision. While it may look like they lost out in a Mexican pizza sale. In reality the Mexican pizza was my reason for stoping at Taco Bell. This was the unique item I could not get anywhere else. Once I was at the window for a Mexican pizza I would then add on the other 6-7 dollars Of menu items. I definitely do not crave an over priced taco or a burrito that has all beans..

text: Food was delicious. Advertised that they close at 9. Called to make sure we could still be seated and have time to eat, and said yes. Seated at 8:45pm and told we had 5 min to order because kitchen is closing. In less than 5 minutes they asked us to go ahead and order. 2 of our 8 orders were wrong. Less than 10 minutes into eating they told us front desk is closed and needed to collect our payment and literally stood over us eating wanting us to sign the receipt. Had to stop eating and sign it to make her get off my shoulder. Never checked on us for refills. I've never been more rushed out of a restaurant in my life. They shouldn't seat people if you aren't going to give us time to eat. Most restaurants we've go into before close, they still let you enjoy a 30-40min meal while they clean up. text: Our family meet here for dinner. we had 2 children with us. when we were given a highchair with a broken strap we asked for another highchair. their employee informed us they were not a family friendly restaurant and only had two highchairs (we were not even offered the other highchair). Also, when our party was seated for dinner at a table the waitress told them that it was happy hour and draft beer was 1/2 price until 7pm. However, when everyone received their bills none of their beers where half price. They were then informed that it was only for those seated in the bar area. Despite our waitress telling us it was half price the manager did not honor the happy hour price. I have never felt so unwelcome at a restaurant. We will not be returning.

name: Joseph Gray
text:
We needed a place to eat that served food past 10:00pm and saw this option.
We started with happy hour margaritas and were warned that they were the sweet frozen margaritas right out of the machine. Just as we had been told, the margaritas were sweet. VEEEERY sweet. Neither of us could finish them. All of this is to say, be prepared if you order the frozen margaritas.
Food: our food came out in a reasonable time after ordering. I had the loaded fries dish with chicken. To me this was nothing special - pretty simple plate. The fries and chicken were smothered in buffalo sauce (which I liked). I got exactly what I expected.
My date got the crab and corn dish, and that was pretty spectacular. The combination was unique and delicious.
One thing I was disappointed in besides the drink was that they charged you for chips and salsa... What??
Overall I'd recommend this for late night eats, but wouldn't seek it out with so many other options nearby with similar special deals on drinks and free chips and salsa.

Trust me it's not worth the time of day. I recommend going anywhere else but here. Reading other comments it's obvious this place has a reputation for awful service. text: Taco Tuesday is rad. Expect a wait, because this place can get pretty busy. Once you get a table, though, you have a selection of a bunch of different soft shell tacos, all $2 each. My favorite was the chicken BLT taco, which tastes like something Chickfila should have, but doesn't. I had a good time here! The staff was friendly, the food was good, and the ice in the water even had little holes in them so us ice-munchers can stab them with our straws. Only things I didn't like about this place was the noise, and the somewhat ugly decor. You've still gotta try this place though.

name: Brad Seehawer
text:
Five Points is a bastion of fine dining and quality nightlife, though some do it better than others, and in the case of Fuego, they're much better at the latter than the former.

In the restaurant's defense, a cantina is more about the drink than the food, and it seems like Fuego does moderately well in this case, providing an inviting atmosphere both inside an out that encourages its patrons to sit and enjoy a drink or three on the patio. But it turns out they have a food menu, too, and it's this food menu from which we ate.

There's a fair amount of options, including a variety of regional burritos - things like California burritos with fries, and a Caribbean jerk chicken burrito, and it's the second of these choices I ate for my meal.

But first, an appetizer. The fried pickled jalapeno slices looked good on paper, and were fried well, but there was a bitterness in the jalapenos that was downright displeasing. They weren't finished.

While blackened jerk chicken may sound appetizing on the menu, the resulting product was standard food service fare, and it was accompanied by some rice and guacamole that tasted like it had been sitting around for a while.

I think the idea for the food menu is to offer something to munch on once you've had a few too many margaritas (and while they're made with a good tequila, it will take quite a few to start feeling it). Fuego's food was lazy, and devoid of conviction. There are plenty of other good dining choices in the area, and there are other good drinking areas, too, leaving Fuego with not much to offer.

name: Soren Diederik
text: My girlfriend and I came in for Taco Tuesday tonight and WOW! Not only was the atmosphere and staff amazing but the tacos are fantastic!! We actually ended up meeting the new owner and he was super nice! They have these new spunky "House Rules" menus that help you navigate through an authentic menu. We had the beef, chicken, and pulled pork tacos  (at $2 each on Tuesday) and I would HIGHLY recommend the queso. We ended up scooping the queso out with our fingers when we ran out of chips (the first time, you get more don't worry). Overall this is a great spot and we definitely look forward to more Taco Tuesdays at Fuego Cantina!!!

name: Berglund15
text: Melanie was awesome. She had a great attitude and everything. Best waitress ever.

name: Allan Elsberry
text:
My friends and I were extremely disappointed with our trip to Fuego. After some decent food we sat at the saloon bar for drinks. While at the bar we took some group pictures of ourselves; however, one bartender flipped out at the possibility that he may be in the background of these photos (maybe the camera will steal your soul?)

The encounter was completely inappropriate. Instead of politely raising his concern, the bartender just starts yelling. My friends and I got the hint that he was unstable, paid the tab and left.

To make matters worse, I had to dispute the charge on my credit card bill because this employee decided to add an extra tip for himself.

I don't plan to ever visit this place again.

name: Brandi Lashai
text: Let me start off by saying how much I love Mexican cuisine. However, if this were the only place in town to get it, I would not go. For starters, they took forever to wait on my party and there were only 3 full tables...on a weekend (that says enough by itself). Secondly, they do no give complimentary salsa and chips like normal Mexican restaurants. While I have no issue paying for it, I do expect it to be fresh and tasteful and it was everything but that. The chips were stale and the salsa tasted like plain tomato juice. Then my queso was cold and thick like a block of Rotel that hasn't been melted thoroughly. The margaritas were disgusting. What Mexican restaurant do you know can't make margaritas...? besides this one. The icing on the cake was when I got my check. The amount with the added gratuity was one amount and then when they brought my ticket and card back I was charged it was a different amount. So I called to dispute it today and was hung up on and denied a manager on several different calls. I am highly upset and I wouldn't recommend that restaurant to my worst enemy. I should've went to The Red Zone...that's where I was supposed to eat.

text: If I could give a no star rating I would. I had dinner on my birthday a few weeks back and had a horrible dining experience at this restaurant. The waitress seated us and did not return to our table until thirty minutes later to take our drink order only. We actually told her that we were ready to order but she left anyways. The bizarre part is that it was a slow evening and she passed by our table about six times but refused to stop after we attempted to wave her over after the fourth time. I almost decided to leave after the initial lack of service but my boyfriend convinced me to stay. However, by the end of the two and a half hour period of delayed service, mediocre food (I ordered the mushroom quesadilla and he ordered the wings with fuego fries - neither were anything special), and attitude from the waitress my boyfriend regretted convincing me to stay. I reported the young lady's lack of professionalism and poor service to the manager via phone the next day. Overall, I will never return to eat or drink at Fuego Cantina because of their horrible quality of customer service and courtesy.

text: My girlfriend a I went to fuegos cantina recently for a taco tuesday special and it was the worst attempt on an edible meal in my opinion. Im a chef my self and when i took one bit of my fuegos "famous" taco i spit it out. The little itty bitty porportion of steak i was given was completely burnt. Charred burnt. We odered 4 of them and every single one was like this and the tortilla it self was not warmed in any way before serving it to a customer. Also we odered a salsa verde and it came out more like a soup verde. The chips given for this green soup were not warmed in any way either. So yeah its a great hangout spot for uab people and students. maybe a good spot for a few drinks but DO NOT EAT THERE. Their kitchen staff needs a serious upgrade.And when i brought it up to the manager she did not offer any retured services for the food being so disgusting except remake the tacos and they came back out just as bad. She also blamed the reason the salsa looked liked soup was because they were not supposed to sell it but one of the mexicans in the kitchen cant speak english. Her words not mine. You get what you pay for on those 2 dollar tacos. Taco bell would have been more appetizing. I run a kitchen that holds a way higher capacity and this place couldnt handle 30 people inside their restraunt. If it wasnt in smack middle of 5 points birmingham nobody would eat there guaranteed. If your in the area try blackmarket or makarios. And what kind of mex-tex restraunt doesnt serve chips and salsa free?

One other table with two guest and still took 20 minutes to get food. Plus 4% charge if you pay with a card. Have eaten here 6 or 7 times,  but this was the first time in months.  Wasn't bad when they first opened, just mediocre and inconsistent. Definitely has taken a turn for the worse. Unfortunate because it is so close.

text:
Waitress was nice, but that wasn’t enough to make up for their food. I had the tacos al pastor, and it left a lot to be desired. The tortillas were stale and cold, the meat was bland and laden with gristle, and the salsa was also bland. The cilantro was old and wilted, and the limes dried and shriveled, as if they’d been cut a week before.
I won’t be back, that’s for sure.

text: Awesome street tacos,chips, guac. Try brisket and pork belly. Everything is really fresh hence the name. Friendly staff and owner, must try, not your typical Mexican restaurant. Great outdoor patio!

name: Rachel Petry
text: Amazing food! Mexican fusion! Delicious and a great neighborhood treasure!

name: Jill Byrd
text: Beautifully plated cuisine. My friend’s beef brisket enchiladas had little flavor; the meat or the mole sauce. It looked amazing but needed more spice and salt. I ordered shrimp street tacos. Everything individually was wonderful, but the shrimp came served in a bowl with tails still on and the pineapple salsa, tomatillo sauce, slaw all were separate. A little cumbersome to peel grilled medium size shrimp and assemble the taco on a rectangular plate. I opted to just try to eat the last of the shrimp without the tiny tortilla. I ordered guacamole as a side with my tacos which was listed as $3 more. When the bill came, the guacamole was $9. Our lunch with tea & Diet Coke was $52.The tea was served with simple syrup to sweeten. Nice, but strange for a Mexican restaurant or any restaurant in the south.  Not really practical for most people ,and while the food was obviously fresh, it was lacking.

name: Mary Alice Kline
text: This is the best Mexican restaurant I have ever experienced. Everything single thing our party of four ordered was fantastic, fresh, and made from scratch. The drinks were amazing. Lots of vegetarian options. The service was excellent. It’s the best Mexican restaurant in Birmingham by far. A must try and new go-to. It’s the Mexican version of Hot & Hot and Highlands.

name: Logan Burgess
text:
No sombreros or Mariachis here. Feels more like a restaurant you’d find in Mexico City than in Alabama. The menu is small but everything is excellent. They have a fantastic tequila selection and tequila flights.

I also appreciated the vintage Mexican movies on the TVs for ambience.

name: Heather Joe
text: Mexican street corn dip is soooo good. Enjoyed the black bean and mushroom tacos. All the toppings with the sauce and slaw was wonderful. Vegetarian friendly and very tasty. Great wine and tequila list.

name: Jason Dahlberg
text: We have dined at Fresco twice now. The first experience was understandably average (because they had only been open for 1 Month). The second experience was more recent and an absolute disappointment. We  purposely came on a quiet night, hoping for better service and product. Such a let down. Service was worse than average, it was nonexistant. Management seemed clueless. Pork belly tacos were over-cooked and tasted like old fry oil. Queso casserole looked good but carried absolutely no flavor. Ultimately, this place is over-priced for less than average product and worse management. Don’t waste your time.

name: LeNell Camacho Santa Ana
text: Lived in Mexico. Best salsa in town. The borracho is spot on. Pork from Bama's Spencer Farm.  Cocktails creative and balanced. The roasted oysters had me licking the shells clean so dang delicious. Not the average local Tex Mex cheap version of Mexico. So good I asked if owners are Mexican.

Furthermore, apparently, “el Zun Zun” refers to a certain hummingbird species. Is it a silly coincidence that Fresco’s logo is a hummingbird? Too many people have lost money in the cursed shadow of Dairy Queen.

name: Tina Connell
text: Honestly , I do not know how this restaurant has not been shut down by health department. On top of the fact a TV Mexican dinner would have been more appetizing and less hassle. We ordered, our food and one beer. A different server brought the beer and had two, we explained we only ordered one. When food was brought to table by another  server. We waited for our server to bring us silverware, by the time I decided to get it myself our food was cold. My husband asked for tea from each server that came to our table and I asked for tea when I requested silverware. I had to go find tea pitcher myself. No one asked if they could help, and when we where done and wondering if we were going to get our Check. Our server showed up, my husband explained,  no everything was not okay. We had to get our on silverware, our on drinks. Her response was not, apologetic at all. Her response was well we had a large party. I saw the other patrons in the restaurant, while I was getting our silverware and my husband’s tea. There is no excuse, for poor service. We had to wait at cash register, until I waved a waiter down and told him I had a list of complaints but all I would like to do is pay my bill. When the hostess came to the register with a attitude, she tried to charge us for the two beers. We both told her, one we had one beer. Along with our other experience. She left the register, then came back with the original bill we were given by our so called server. The cashier was rude and had an attitude on top of that. So to sum up our experience the food was bad, the service was bad, and the restrooms were nasty. I would not recommend this place, it is obvious they do not care about quality. The booth behind us, were not served more than chips and drinks, they left. A table across from us had to get their on silverware also. The only reason I give one star, was in iorder to leave a review.

resp.text: Tina, I am so deeply sorry to hear of this news. We've been working diligently over the last few weeks to improve all areas of our restaurant. I sincerely hope that you'll visit us again, and notify a manager immediately. You, just like all other patrons of our restaurants deserve nothing but the best and we want to give you just that! We were going through some major growing pains, and while that is no excuse, it's important for me to inform you and anyone else reading this that the experience you described above is not our norm. This does not set well with us but we are thankful for your feedback and will not take your concerns lightly. Thanks again.

text: I understand that this is fast food so I wasn't expecting much,but I was surprised at the level of rudeness, and how dirty everything was. The food was very bland and I thought overpriced for what we got, but I wasn't prepared for the sticky floors, dirty tables, and filthy drink station at 11:00 in the morning. The young lady taking orders was very apathetic and borderline rude. To bad a one star is as low as I can rate it. If this is a one, I guess Taco Bell is a five.

text: Yummy food! My husband had the mango barbacoa (?) burrito which he loved. I had the southwest pork ranch bowl. It was really good,  but spicy! Nice, clean place, and the staff was friendly. I’d definitely go back, but get the smaller bowl size.

resp.text: Thank you for the great review Gabby. Can't wait until you back it back!

name: Justin B.
text: Awesome food and friendly staff! So much variety in flavor and the ingredients are pretty high quality. It's nice to finally find a place with a lot of flavor. Try the hothead sauce with the steak burrito. Also, the spicy sauce is good, maybe not hot enough for some, but most people will like it. I'm only sad that I'm graduating and moving to a place without this great new restaurant. Try it and you won't be disappointed.

resp.text: Thank you for your review Justin. It's sad to hear you're moving away from but anytime you come back we would love to see you again! Have a good day.

name: Noemi Cole
text: The food is awesome! You have a variety to choose from and everything has a lot of flavor. Everytime I have gone the staff has been super friendly and on top of their job. They even go as far as checking up on how the food was and saying goodbye as we're walking out. It is also squeaky clean, which is always a good sign.

resp.text: Thank you for the great review Noemi!

name: Rustin Haywood
text: Great tacos and bowls. Great selection of toppings and different hot sauces from sweet to super spicy. $2 tacos on Tuesdays. Generous amount of queso for $1 If you want it added to a bowl. All of the ingredients seem very fresh and the staff is pretty happy to help most of the time.

resp.text: Thank you for the great review!

text: Good food...sad to see that if you get a bowl, you have to purchase chips.  A dollar extra for this or that and then you have a rather pricey meal for what you get.  It is good, though.

resp.text: Instead of getting a bowl next time maybe get nachos and just ask for the chips on the side! Glad to hear that you liked the food though, hope to see you back soon!

name: J “JThe Fifth” Five
text:
Food is Okay, nothing special. but let me tell you...

Chips: they charge for them and give you and your friend the tiniest amount of chips in human history (When I say 7 chips each, I'm not kidding)

Salsa: I swear to you a side of Salsa is.. drum roll.. $1.20!!!!! Yes one dollar and twenty cents.

Rewards program: 1 point for each Item. 12 points until you get a reward. Well I just want a burrito so 12 visits?? you are out of your mind!

text: Staff was friendly and their specials are good. Food was a little bland and the chips tasted store-bought but I'd still go again for the atmosphere and fat burritos if I had another coupon. Probably wouldn't pay full price for this though.

resp.text: Thanks for the review

text: The staff was nice enough, but the food was pretty bland. The parts of the bowl that I expected to be hot, were cold (i.e the meat) and there wasn't much flavor, even after adding sauce. Considering there are so many other options in the area for amazing Mexican food, I'll pass.

text: Service was kind of slow and every person on the line seemed distracted (an employee asked what kind of meat I would have and then dumped chicken on it before I could answer) but I can look past that since they had just opened. The food was beyond bland and the corn salsa was pretty much canned yellow corn. Most of the sauces are more sweet/something you would put on barbecue rather than a burrito. Weirdly, they kind of skimped on rice and don't drain the black beans so my burrito was pretty soggy in the end as well

No matter how many sauces I added to my bowl it tasted like nothing and this was on 3 different occasions. The barbacoa is good and the customer service is good but this place is not comparable to Moe's or Chipotle when it comes to flavor.

text: Great tasting food at reasonable prices. Lots of daily deals like Taco Tuesday where you get $2 tacos. I had the barbacoa burrito and it was delish, kind of like mexican roast beef. Staff was pretty friendly as well. We will definitely be back.

resp.text: Travis thank you for taking your time to leave a review it is greatly appreciated. We are glad to hear that you enjoyed your visit to Hot Head and we are glad to hear we will be seeing you again! Have a nice day!

text: Great place! It's hard to not reveiew this place without comparing it to Chipotle which has been in Auburn/Opelika longer. The reason I'd mention it is to say it's better than Chipotle. Prices are comparable but the ingredients are even better. They have more options as well: multiple tortillas, more veggies, more sauces, and sizes of the burritos and bowls (meaning you can get smaller versions.) I'll definitely be going back.

name: Desmond Boswell
text:
**The good:
- price (check out Facebook promotions for a better deal)
- variety of ingredients & sauces
- lots of options for people who do and don't like spicey food
- location (near the Auburn mall)
- quick in and out
**Cons:
- if you order online, expect less food (bowls)
- The containers were all plastic, which is an environmental nightmare. They now just have plastic tops for the bowls, but still.
- They got rid of pineapple as a choice

TLDR: Great quick and spicey Mexican style food. Avoid online ordering to not get shorted food.

resp.text: Thank you for the great review!

text:
Honestly, its not bad! You dont automatically get chips,guac and cheese are $1  extra.
The selection of sauces to put on your burrito/taco/ bowl are amazing. Prices arent too bad since its very filling. I just cand find a reason to give it all 5 stars - but the staff was pretty nice and it was clean. This is good considering how new it is.

name: Seth Humphrey
text: Really good and fast food.  This is a new restaurant for Auburn/Opelika and comes with more options than we're used to at "tell-me-how-you-want-your-mexi-food-fixed places" and therefore most customers are much slower at placing their orders but the staff is very friendly and helpful to guide you into making good choices.  The pork bowl with salsa verde, corn, and sweet habanero sauce is killer good.  Chips/salsa cost extra just like Chipotle, but overall the food is better, more flavorful (like 20 sauce choices), and lower price point.  To knock it out of the park, this place serves Pepsi unlike most places in town.  This is my daughter's new favorite place to eat (doesn't hurt that kids get a cookie, coloring sheets, stickers, and tattoos).  Two more things I love as a parent: 1) no TVs so you have to look at each other and talk, and 2) really clean bathrooms.  Thanks Hot Head Burritos!

The salad with our fajitas was 100% fresh. The rice & beans= perfect. The fajitas were delicious & an order for one was enough for two. Quality chicken & steak. The cheese dip (my favorite) was very good & thick. The large was 20 oz. for $8. This is my new favorite Mexican restaurant & I highly recommend.cost of meal shown in photos= $22

text: Excellent! Will be back for sure! Chicken tacos were very good, just the right amount of spice, and juicy chopped chicken. Taste of the chicken was almost like a bbq'd chopped chicken with a Mexican flare. Fries were very good with a spicy seasoning on top. I highly recommend stopping by for lunch when you're tired of seafood. Absolutely no complaints. I enjoy giving good reviews when they're worth it.

name: Ryan McVay
text: Really good tacos. May not be the best tacos I've ever had, but definitely top three. You really can tell that they use fresh ingredients. The cashier was very, polite, knowledgeable about the food, helpful, and very nice. It's both difficult and easy to find. If you're familiar with the area, you shouldn't have a problem. But if you're not so familiar with the area, and all the little plazas around the restaurant. You may find it difficult to locate. Here's a hint it's right behind McDonald's, if you're traveling north on Juniper Street. I definitely would recommend this to anyone who enjoys a good shrimp or fish taco, or good food in general.

name: Jessea Negless (StreetFire)
text: We tried this local taco joint while visiting due to good reviews. The place was clean and staff friendly. Nice menu selection. We got the fish tacos and steak tacos. The fish was definitely the best! If returning that's what I'd get again and recommend. The steak taco and hot mess beans were bland in our opinion. The guac was really good.  I'd be up for trying some chicken tacos as another diner said they were really good.

name: Larry McJunkin
text:
I love Mexican food. In fact, it's my very favorite of any cuisine, and I've eaten it all over the world, including Mexico. The tacos I had today in Bravo Tacos had a lot of potential, but they were made of ground beef that was either slightly old or perhaps had a spice in it that didn't agree with me. I ordered two tacos with beans and rice and ordered one hard shell and one soft shell. Both came with soft shells. Not a big deal, but not what I ordered, and they were not busy. The black beans and rice were very sticky.

I only ate part of one taco since it didn't taste good. I returned to our rental condo and felt a little sick to my stomach about an hour later. I took some Pepto Bismol, which cleared it up quickly. I'm not directly blaming the taco meat, but I do think it was more than coincidental this happened shortly after eating it, especially since it had a taste that didn't seem quite right.

I really liked the restaurant ambiance a lot, and I think it's probably a good place, but it just wasn't a good experience for me.

name: David Morgan
text: Go here every time I go to Orange Beach. Amazing food, decent service. I've been told everything is homemade and of the highest quality. It certainly tastes that way. Get the fish tacos, you won't regret it.

name: Kim McElderry
text: Cool little place. Order at the counter. Take-out or dine-in.

name: Jason Kay
text: Tried to go here on Thursday but they were closed...at 4 pm for "summer hours". Summer hours?? During peak tourist season in August and you close at 4 pm?! I went next door to Pizza Hut and got some pizza in 10 minutes. I'm not sure the reason for your summer hours but people generally eat after 4 pm.

name: Aaron Anttila
text: We're from Texas where we have great tacos everywhere. A little nervous about eating tacos in Alabama but wow they make some great taco here. Would eat here again in a heartbeat. 6 people in our party and all agreed. Eat it!

name: Zach Rutledge
text: Nice folks and great food make this something of a hidden gem on Canal Road in Orange Beach.  They offer only tacos and burritos, really, but they do them very, very well.  The sauces are excellent, too.

name: Chris Hill
text: Great tacos! I went with the combo with one fish and one shrimp taco. They both were a good balance of spicy and fresh. The liquado for an extra buck was worth it too - very refreshing. After talking to the owner and hearing their story, I will be back. Only let down: location is next to a gas station.

name: Jennifer Sims
text:
Local spot that always hits the spot!
Generous portions, great food, friendly service and always fresh. Have never tried something here I didn't like, only things I like better than others.
You literally can't go wrong on any choice.
I really like the fish tacos, they have a pineapple slaw on them that adds just enough sweetness...the guacamole is really good too-more peppery than limey which I find unique, and my latest favorite is the chicken costa-rican. Hubby always gets the chicken burrito and can rarely finish it off.
Standard salsa is more smokey/mesquite than traditional tomato, but they do offer a variety of options, so just know ahead of time if you're someone that doesn't like smokey salsa.
Love this place and come here often. Check it out!

name: Tori Navigator
text:
Generous portions, delicious flavor and spice on the meat, and always fresh. Hot mess is amazing. Don't miss the hot mess.
We rode our bikes afterwards to burn off some calories. Ha!

text: Not expecting this to be so good!  Delicious! Very helpful guy at the counter!

text: Great little place to enjoy fresh food, great selections. Fish taco's, steak taco's, the mushroom dish, all were well done. Will make another trip during our week here.

text: I crave these tacos. Eveything is fresh and the salsa is amazing. Super nice people too.

name: Bird Davidson (Bird)
text: Fresh delicious food that has never disappointed. Love the fish tacos, fresh squeezed liquado, and Bravo nachos!

name: apacheav8rix
text:
We stumbled upon this place one Saturday and we eat here as often as possible. Every order is made fresh to order, all the ingredients are fresh and NOT processed. The carnitas have a wonderfully savory flavor, the salsas are each unique and flavorful. This is what food tastes like when it's made with love! Bravo Taco is the only reason we drive from Pensacola to Orange Beach, every chance we get. The staff is knowledgable, professional, hard working. I've asked about their hours before (11-4) and it's so limited because they can't find people to work with so many businesses in the area also hiring anyone breathing.
My only complaint about Bravo Taco is that I always get mad because the food is so delicious I want to eat more but I can't physically consume anymore. Guaranteed to over-eat, every time.

name: M Parker
text: AWFUL!!!!! I ate there with my husband. They should have been ashamed of what they served. The shrimp and steak were cold. The tacos were sitting in water, which made them soggy and disgusting. The sides were to salty to eat. They charged me full price for guacamole, they served in a small side cup. I heard them saying they were out of the reg cups, just use the small ones, it doesn't matter...The staff made comments about what we ordered. So we paid $40 for food that we had to throw away. I sent an email to the owner, who NEVER replied. That is not how you treat your customers! I work in Orange Beach and eat here everyday...they lost a customer. I also work where visitors are constantly asking me where to eat...I will NEVER recommend this place. If they ask me about Bravo, I tell them my story!

text: After waiting a whole year I found out this location has gotten 10x worse I went to purchase food today from this location when I got home and looked at the food it looked horrible the taco was soggy and the quesadilla was burnt and to add on they got my two supreme tacos wrong and when I went to return them after biting half of one and realizing it wasn’t what I paid for the lady asked for the food back which was a big NO NO with COVID-19 and other viruses you should never receive food that has been in someone else’s possession and I witnessed other employees opening the food which I had took bites out of and still preparing food (CROSS-CONTAMINATION!!) The employee and manager refused to give me two supreme tacos because one had been bitten out of and I got shorted my money because she did not give me the taco I had took a bite out of and after I received the replacement I did not feel like eating it because of the cross-contamination. This is a breeding ground for all types of illnesses the window they are serving out of has dirt piled on it and finger smudges and from what I’m told this is nothing new. Every single one of the afternoon shift employees (and managers) need to get retrained on their customer service skills and cross-contamination.

The employees here are a disgrace and it's amazing that they were even able to land a job in the first place. It's really a sad thing to see.

So we went inside and waited nearly another 10 minutes for a single burrito to be made. Customer service was severely lacking. The dude didn't ask if we need any sause, he just threw some mild in the bag and expected it to be good. When we asked for a different sause he handed us waaaay to many, and seemed irritated that i even asked. I understand fast food is awful to work, but there's still like a low level of expectations to be met and they were not met in any fashion during my visit. My remade burrito wasn't even wrapped properly, and was falling apart. Overall, a very disappointing visit. I'd swerve for a other tacobell in the area or something.

text: The owner Jose made the visit awesome. We only had chips salsa queso and frozen margaritas but everything was delicious. Can't wait to go back and order a meal. Maybe then it may be a 5 star instead of 4.

text: Fresh food, good service. Lunch buffet has a decent amount of variety and the food is better than many Mexican buffets. Ordering off the menu at lunch is reasonably fast. They have a nice variety of dishes on the menu.

name: Kween “Simpli Fenixx” Bedhead
text: My husband and I went to Las Parillas for lunch for the very first time today.. When we entered the establishment we were greeted with no salutation other then "How many". The hostess proceeded to pick up some silverware and speed away. Not sure if we were supposed to follow her or not because she didn't tell us to we stood for a moment confused.. Her attitude was sour instantly leaving a bad taste in my mouth. The service after that point didn't get any better. The food was cold and I wasn't impressed with the selection. I could go on but I will just leave it at this.. I won't be going back again and I only have one star cause it wouldn't let me write a review without it.. To the hostess, thank for the compliment about my nails when we were leaving but um. it was a day late and a dollar short. Had you been polite from the beginning you wouldn't be on my crap list..

name: Shonta Dillard
text: I visited for the first time on a Monday during happy hour. The server wasn't listening, rushed me to order, the frozen daiquiri was NOT!!!! I asked them to correct the drink, it was still very juicy. The taco salad was something I never seen before, more toppings than meat, it couldn't have been beef. I just paid for the food and left. Never coming back. The only reason this has 2 stars from me is because the prices were reasonable and they sell alcohol. But ill never go back.

name: Brooke Graham
text: After going to Rosie's and Guadalajara, both had 45 min to an hour long wait!, we made our way to Las Parillas.  All positive remarks, I did just give 4 stars because their salsa was very bland.  But, prompt service, great entrees. They offer a margarita pitcher option.  I had the enchiladas verde - the sauce was great!  My friend is a vegetarian and she had multiple options to chose from which made her happy.  After our meal, we sat in the lounge to finish our pitcher and watch a soccer game.  All the good Mexican beer on tap :) I'll definitely be back to chill in the lounge

name: Michael McCorvey

name: Chevi Kimbrel
text: The food seemed so bland, it had absolutely no seasoning. The salsa was so extremely spicy, that I assumed they gave us their most spiciest by mistake. I asked if they had a mild one, the server said yes & brought me enchilada sauce & 2 more of the exact same salsa. 🙄 The salsa almost seemed like it was tomato purée, with straight jalapeño🤷🏼‍♀️. There was NO cilantro or any other seasoning that I could taste. The rice was super hard and clunked together like it had been sitting on a hot station for a good period of time & maybe dried out. We asked if we could substitute the “guacamole salad” for sour cream vs Guacamole - the server said yes, but brought us guacamole. He was supposed to bring us sour cream and chips back & I think he forgot about us until we got the check. He was suppose to bring us some chips for - we ordered 2 cheese dips & the chips they provided was crushed up and crumbles. Which really didn’t matter since the cheese dip was cold. I tried to explain to the server, but I don’t think he understood. He would just say “yes” & nod his head. I love to support local & hope this may be a fluke with just starting out or maybe just one of those nights. I sincerely hope it improves and has many successful years. Tonight was a total waste of money & filled with disappointments.

text: We eat here once a week, and it is always wonderful.  The food is fresh and tasty, and the service is personable and efficient.  Love it!

name: mario herrera
text:
My wife Jacqui and I enjoy eating at Las cazuelas. The Mexican cuisine restaurant is handicappped accessible. The floors are shinny. The tables are neatly arranged and the restrooms are clean. I am especially pleased at the bilingual waitstaff. Enzio, Reinaldo and Jose Antonio. The waiters are polite, courteous and really interact with me on Hispanic cultures, traditions and customs. Every time we go to Las Cazuelas there is a friendly atmosphere, high quality meals at reasonable prices. Jacqui and I know we can dine at our leisure. We are never rushed. Waiters check on our table without intruding.
The menus are clear, concise and printed in a colorful style. Jacqui and I travel 25 miles to eat at Las Cazuelas. We'll return soon. Mario A. Herrera, world traveler.

name: Javier Suarez
text: Excellent Food, Friendly Service! One of my favorite hangouts in Mobile, AL.

name: Curt Crider
text:
We had a very nice time at Las Cazuelas last night. Karoake was in full swing, the margaritas were good, and the entrees and a-la-carte were satisfying. We really liked the grilled fish tacos, chicken quesadillas were consumed with gusto, the chips and salsa were unending. This is a family eatery with several large tables for groups, booths for smaller groups, and some smaller tables.

The staff has always been pleasant and we always have a good time.

name: Will Trahan
text:
Ordered the enchiladas supremos, which comes with 4 different enchiladas: cheese, chicken, beef, and bean.  Positively the best tasting cheese enchilada I've ever had. Other reviews find the food bland, but I was happy with the seasoning.  I was able to taste the food without any excessive flavors or spices.  For reference, I'm from South Louisiana and I both know and appreciate excessive "hotly spiced" foods and think jalapenos make any food better.  The lettuce was freshly crisp and cold along with the sour cream, which surprised me for how hot the plate was and not trying either for a few minutes after receiving my food.

I'm not usually a fan of chips and salsa but I ate half the basket before forcing myself to stop or I wouldn't be able to eat my meal.  The salsa was flavorful and had a small kick.  The service was attentive without being overbearing.

The sopapilla with ice cream is a meal by itself in size.  They were delicious with the drizzled chocolate and honey with some sugar as well

The vibe to me is quiet, not too dimly lit but I know some people might have trouble with reading the menu where I was sitting.
