text: The food and the service was awesome

name: Phil Dye
text: Absolutely delicious! The quesadilla Mexicana was the best I have had and my wife really enjoyed the quesadilla fajita. Great cheese deep too. Jimena was a great waitress and ensured we were taken care off. Will absolutely come back.

name: Tracy Reynolds
text: We love this place! Gotta try the Chili Relleno and Gringa, they are amazing!

name: annette bramblett
text: Always great food and great service.  Dont normally get to make lunch time but the buffet was Very good.....even had Flan for dessert.  Heavenly.

name: Christine Jones
text: Great Mexican food. You can order from the menu or eat from the buffet. We always have a great experience here!

name: Maya Bailey
text: Great Mexican Cuisine, highly recommend!

name: torri clayton
text: Got to try this little gem while visiting family in the area.  I loved the super friendly staff and cozy atmosphere! i was a little impressed with the menus mix of the expected (think beef tacos) and unexpected (pineapple and pork options!). Everything was tasty and our service was surprisingly quick for how busy they were. We will definitely be back on our next visit!

name: Raymond Watson
text: The bean dip for the chips absolutely scrumptious. I can’t get enough of their food. Customer service is great. Very friendly and inviting environment.

name: Jennifer Ferrero
text: The food was delicious! The portions are generous for the prices per dish. The chips and salsa at the beginning were so good, too! My hubby and I are definitely going back whenever we get our next craving for Mexican food~

name: Rell Global
text: Nice environment!

name: Sheri Spuhl
text: Service was fair, not good.  No silverware on the table & we asked 3 times before getting any.  Had to ask for a drink refill.  Food was bland. Hubby got some kind of street looking tacos. Meh. I ordered a chicken enchilada plate. Got beef.  Asked if the waiter could change it.  He did. To shredded beef!  Asked again. Got the chicken enchilada & asked for a to-go box. We shared hubby's plate & had my dinner for lunch the next day. There are several Mexican restaurants,  so we will choose another one from now on. So much for branching out!

name: Janay Battles
text: Food is flavorful and the drinks are delicious. Happy hour is 7 days a week with all day specials 3 days out of the week. Definitely one of the best Mexican restaurants in Huntsville.

name: Frank Wagner
text: Three out of five orders were wrong. Food bland and not tasty. I recommend ordering somewhere else.

name: Rory Crews
text: I had the same experience as the reviewer “Sheri” had three weeks ago.  The waitress acted like she was in mourning for someone and very well could have been...sad, no hello, no smiling.  The place is clean, modern, and fresh smelling.  The head waiter was friendly.  Salsa was very bland.  Carnitas fries were good.  Lunch burrito was bland.  The lettuce and tomatoes with the burrito were fresh.  The unsweet tea was not good, so I got a Coke to replace it.  Might give it a second try in the future.

name: Mike Keck
text: I had the chicken burrito plate. It came with rice and beans. I also had them add chorizo to my burrito. It was all outstanding. The included salsa and chips were also top of the line.

name: lesley johnson
text: Me and kids have been eating here for years and I’ll never eat here again. Ordered from grub hub and got one teaspoon of beans, the shrimp was bland, I ordered flour tortillas and got corn tortillas, the rice was dry with no seasoning. Over all a very bad experience that I don’t want to encounter again.

name: Kecia Pierce
text: Good food, good service and great margaritas!

name: Rafael Negron Torres
text: Came to the Olmeca the other day and this is why I keep coming back. The Ribeye fajitas are my favorite. Can't get any better than this.

name: Karen Moore
text: We had delivery last night and it was amazing!!! Definitely will try again

name: Marc Harms
text: Great food and service. My Mexican wife was pleased, and she's quite picky with Mexican restaurants. The only thing preventing a 5 star rating:  the rice was sub-par (on all of my visits) especially when contrasted with the quality of the other food.  Also, the queso dip tastes right but is far too thin.  My favorite so far has been their taco al pastor and any of their carnita dishes.  I would highly recommend eating here if you're in the mood for some Mexican.

name: Christina Beal
text: This is such a fun place. Love the food and drinks and people. Wonderful service and great atmosphere.

name: Raychel Zygula
text: Best Mexican hole-in-the-wall this side of the River. Very authentic, decently priced, great service. Reminds me of home!

name: Ron King
text: Great food and experience, the menu had some unique items not seen in other mexican restaurants.  The atmosphere was not overwhelming, music at a decent level.  We will visit here again

name: Michael D'Auben
text: A really excellent Mexican restaurant with a selection beyond the typical Mexican restaurant fare.  Service has always been excellent too.  One of my favorites.

name: Darrin Gainer
text: Came up from Florida for a funeral,  needed a break. The food was EXCELLENT!  A great relaxing experience.

name: Matt Davies
text: Great food, great service. Easily the best Mexican in town.

name: Abigail Cunningham
text: This is my favorite more traditional Mexican around (so like excluding Taco Mama)!  Their chips, salsa, and queso are always on point, and their frozen margaritas are the best!  Seriously worth driving by at least 5 other Mexican restaurants for me!

name: Misty Brooks
text: I wouldn't give this place a star! My husband and I stopped for a drink and a couple tacos. The server charged for a large Margarita, and we were told because we questioned the charge it would be best we didn't come back. We never caused a scene, just enjoying each others company quietly.

name: Makenzi Brandenburg
text: The service was good and everything came out fast. I personally thought that the enchilada sauce tasted more like pasta sauce and that's the only reason for 4 stars!

name: Fred Crow
text: Love this place. It's in my top three Mexican restaurants in Madison county. Their prices are good, the food is excellent and the service is usually wonderful. They have the best salsa in the business.

name: Maurice
text: Do not know how the food is because we never got to seat. My family and I were waiting for 15 minutes and never were acknowledged. Two other parties came and and they spoke Spanish and they were seated before us finally they said, are you waiting on your order?” Why bring in your whole family just to pick up an order. I would not recommend them to anyone during a rush

name: Fealor Herb
text: Good drinks, good food, but my favorite is the people here

name: Edward Davis
text: Service was incredible food was great.

name: Jennifer Davis
text: Loved it! We were originally going to have sushi, but saw this place tucked away in the corner. It was a beautiful night, so we decided to sit outside. It was around Halloween so they had the outside decorated, which was pretty cool. Most restaurants when you sit outside in the patio, they forget about you. Our server never forgot about us and always came to see whether we were doing alright. Plus, the food was amazing , affordable , and plentiful. You get a lot for a little at this place! Plus, the Margaritas were only $2.99 , Which is less expensive than most Mexican restaurants even during happy hour. This It's a new favorite place!

name: Kris Hunter (Lastsonofzod)
text: Great variety, friendly servers, and fast service. Great place!

name: Jeff Hendricks
text: Always excellent service

name: Anthony S
text: Food, ambiance perfect. Was going to buffalo wild wings and the smell drove us to El Olmeca.  Thank goodness...

name: emory winters
text: Love this place. Great food. Great service. Salsa is delicious. Trivia on Wednesdays is fun. Great happy hour specials.

name: Maria C Fairchild
text: Was not bad enjoyed lunch there

name: Dominique Ponder
text: Good food. Great friendly fast service

name: Jeff Martin
text:
This is my favorite Mexican restaurant in town. Everyone there is super friendly and they've actually become my friends and they know me by name.

I sometimes go to eat there when they restaurant is slow (2pm-3pm) with my wife and bring our toddler son. We're regulars there and the staff loves him and will play with him so mom and dad can actually eat and enjoy our meal.

Good happy hour drinks too. Very good margaritas and there's soccer on TV.

name: Sharon Walker
text: Pinto beans are phenomenal!

name: Helen West
text: Food is amazing! Salsa was the best I've had around town. I had the Fajitas Cancun and it is was delicious. My new favorite restaurant!

name: Dan Chivers
text: This is our favorite Mexican place in town.  The food is great and service is good as well.  The waiters and waitresses go out of their way to make sure your visit is a good one.  We would recommend going here if your looking for a good relaxing Mexican restaurant.

name: The Stever’s
text: Love this place this is my go to Mexican restaurant while in Quarantine!

name: Kory And Marty Alfred
text: Food was great! Service was a little slow

name: Joseph Bliss
text: Madison has more than it's fair share of Mexican Restaurants, but El Omeca stands out. Great food and great service.

name: Raychel R. Zygula
text: El Olmeca- Spanish for GOOD!! Closest to authentic Mexican I have found in town. Family friendly atmosphere, very nice staff. Highly recommended for the price. ¡Que bueno!

name: Tim Harrison
text: I didn't go to El Olmeca.  I went to the Four Leaves Asian Restaurant right next door. On Tuesday they have appetizers for half price. My wife and I each had California Chicken rolls and Crab Rangoon. We should have just got one order of the Rangoon as you get 6 to an order. Everything was very good. Two cokes, two Rangoon, and two chicken rolls came to $21.26.

name: Regenia Prater
text: Food was great and service was excellent

name: Lawrence Crawford
text: Most unfriendly service of any restaurant in town.  Brought our family for the lunch buffet, they charged for our three year old (even though three and under are supposed to be free) and charged our ten year old as an adult.  After speaking with a manager who interchangeably said “under 10” and “ten and under” during the conversation, they refused to honor their own printed age of “kids 10 and under”.  Manager was completely unconcern and seemed very happy to hear me say that we would not be back.  He hardly even looked up from his phone.  Total bill for lunch was $53 plus tax and tip.  There are MANY Mexican restaurants in town, so no need to go here again.

name: PeaceMaker Band
text: Great quality food at a great price

name: Jimmy Romines
text: Excellent lunch buffet on Sundays.  Fried shrimp, taquitos, fajita veggies/meat, enchiladas, fruit, and rice are all available and delicious.  For desert, they have charros, cinnamon sugar chips, and fried cream cheese stuffed tortillas with honey and icing available for garnishment.  Over all, fantastic lunch buffet.

name: Michael Pukish
text: This place is the real deal.  Best I've had in Huntsville so far, and more authentic than most of the places i knew in CA.  Homemade chips.  Many authentic dishes on the menu, many that you probably haven't seen before but should definitely try.  One example of what's different here:  They know the difference between pork that is merely roasted, and that which is marinaded.

name: John Martin
text: Family owned and operated. Great food at a good price. Not only chips and salsa, but a small dish of bean dip. Wow, it's a hit. It's a weekly favorite now. Bueno.

name: David Wilson
text: Favorite Mexican restaurant in town. Consistently good food/drink and great service. Seems like I go every week!

name: Thomas Black
text: Quick and friendly service.  Good kids menu. Clean dinning room.   I thought the meat in the Carne Asada Tacos was a little over cooked.

name: veronica maples
text: The best tacos is alabama. Only the one by kroger on 72 in huntsville.

name: Clyde Barrow
text: Great place, stopped here just because it was close by. So glad we did, big portions, friendly staff and good food. Tried the fajitas and enchiladas both were awesome. Will definitely be back.

name: Diego Covarrubias
text: From a Latino perspective and plenty of experience trying different restaurants, this is probably the worse restaurant I been to. The service was 2/10 and the food was 2/10. Was highly disappointed...

name: Moody Harvey
text: My wife and I love this place. Been going there since they opened. We k,ow the wait staff will do a great job and the owners are always friendly. Good food, good pricing, and great service.

name: Pwncake Ironfarts
text: I've been here time after time on my lunch break, as I work just down the road. It's a great place to eat. Atmosphere is good, but not overdone, every plate I've ordered came out tasting fresh and delicious. Their buffet is mostly good, though there was one time that they seemed to just forget it existed and didn't restock it for the 30 minutes I was there. Other than that one time, though, it's always been fresh and well stocked. Staff is always smiling and friendly, and they're willing to make adjustments to plates for allergies or preferences. Solid restaurant. I will continue to eat here for as long as I work near it.

name: david levine
text: Great authentic Mexican. The chef is the best.. And Oscar does a great job running the place.. Awesome lunch specials..

name: joe D
text: The food is great just like the service. My go to for Mexican food.

name: Hobbs 21
text: Well I only got carry out but the food was really good. My only regret was that I didn't get more to last for a second meal.

name: Tophmidna O
text: This place serves a buffet at lunch (11:00-2:00) for a real good price. I would certainly recommend this to anyone who loves queso and Mexican food. Service was good too. A server came by and checked on my often and refilled my chips and my drink almost as soon as they went empty.

name: Mike Colwell
text: Outstanding service and food was amazing!

name: Rosemary Hancock
text: Food was average. I went for Margarita Monday. Service was fine. Everything was just average.

name: gerald Howard
text: The staff and management was were great. My wife and I arrived to eat 25mins before closing time. They did NOT rush us at all and serviced us as if it were 3o'clock in the afternoon. The food was delicious and plentiful!!

name: David Grimes
text: Awesome food and margaritas

name: Gina Satterlee
text: Great place

name: Christina Walker
text: Great food excellent service

name: Cynthia Butler
text: While prices and food was good the service wasnt very friendly.1

name: Courtney Lavenant
text: They have a late night crowd they do on the weekends. Friends went here saturday night and only one of them was given a “blue ticket” to retrieve free drink from the bar. Got free drink and ended up roofied and almost had to be taken to hospital. Wanted to leave a review so other women knew to watch out here!!!!!!

name: Mel Granger
text:
The service has went down the past few times we went and we seemed mostly ignored by our waitor.

In addition they charged for extra tortillas and cheese without warning that each cost a extra dollar. Over all it feels different now and we won't be returning.

name: Ehrrensmommy
text: It's been over 5 years since I've moved here and by far the best Mexican food I've had.  We've gone at least twice a week for food and drinks.  They even catered our work lunch event.  I can't say anything bad!!!

name: Sharon White
text: I enjoyed eating there I have been there Twice in a week.The bartender is excellent in making margaritas for food is better than any Mexican restaurant I give You A 5 Star

name: Eric Connaisseur
text:
Good food. More like california mexican hybrid. Enchilada sauce is tomato paste and green sauce is jalapeno paste which is typical for the area. Prices are average.

I do keep coming back so it still deserves 4 stars.

name: tanya stringer
text: The food was delicious and the service was fantastic. We just moved from El Paso, Tx and we enjoyed the food a lot. We’ll definitely be back.

name: Edward Blancarte
text: Good prompt service. Chips and salsa are better than majority of restaurants. My Chile Verde was good. Overall good value for the money.

name: Amanda D
text: Absolute best Mexican Restaurant in the Madison/Huntsville area. We go here a lot and the wait staff knows us and are always very friendly and accommodating. If you go on a Friday or Saturday evening be prepared to wait since it is a local favorite.

name: Jeanna Romans
text: Excellent food, enjoyed the atmosphere, clean restaurant, and prompt service.

name: Kenneth Alexander
text: Best guac I've had !

name: Robert Muir
text: Great atmosphere.  Love their margaritas (especially on Thursdays).  Everything I have ever ordered has been excellent.  I eat here often.

name: Cowboy-Lone Esch
text: Good food good service. Karaoke bad.

name: Erica Bridwell
text: This place is yummy!! Great chips and salsa is so good and flavorful. Love the lunch buffet!!

name: John Cooley
text: Great food, served quickly, by courteous  and friendly staff.

name: Beth Christa
text: Really good good! Their steak tacos are delicious!

name: Dorothy Peters
text:
El Olmeca is great mexican food for a great price!

Food 4/5: the quality of ingredients seems to be about average, nothing super spectacular.  However, the large variety of options that they offer is great!  I was also pretty impressed with their taco salad.  Most of the time taco salads are a lot of lettuce and a little bit of chicken and cheese, however here they give you lots of deliciously tender chicken in the salad so it's definitely filling.

Service 4/5: I'm always promptly seated and served, the staff is very friendly and attentive.

Atmosphere 3/5: it's not a place I'd go just to for the atmosphere, but definitely a good choice for food.

Overall they offer great food for a very cheap price.

name: Brooke Howe
text: This is my favorite Mexican restaurant in my area. They have quality Mexican food that comes out fast and the service has always been great. We love playing trivia on Wednesday nights too.

name: Claudia Rhen
text: Love the Mambo Taxi and the Chimichangas Trio!

name: Eric Rivera
text: Very good buffet. They don't sacrifice flavor. Service is always great!

name: Heather Paschall
text: The three stars are a little high, but given that our service was great, three stars are reasonable. She never let our glasses empty, and she was helpful and knowledgeable of of the menu. Now the food, I know this is Alabama... BUT if you are used to tex-mex and I mean the GOOD stuff, I would skip this place. The salsa tasted like diced tomatoes with the occasional bite of cilantro. The food had little to no flavor, whatsoever. I had the tres amigos. It was chicken, shrimp and beef on a.bed of rice. Absolutely NO flavor. But...the service was great! The husband got carne asada. It came out as one solid piece of flavorless beef. The rice had NO flavor.

name: K Wynn, the Conscious Lifestyle Enthusiast
text: Really enjoy this restaurant; great food, music, and drinks. The pricing is very reasonable in comparison to other places. The only thing I have an issue with is the stinch of sewage while sitting on the patio kills the mood. Please management address this issue immediately and bring back the patio DJ.

name: scott jennings
text: Quality of the food is consistently good quality and the wait staff is friendly.

name: Jerrold Tucker
text: Always a great time and even better food!

name: Kipp Woodard
text: Great menu. Good service.

name: Susan Levine
text: We are regulars, at least a few times a week.  My fave is Tacos El Pastor.  The chef is consistent and the service is great!

name: Utz Recke
text: Really delicious! I had a rather simple dish: carne assada. Each component made with love and perfection.

name: Kim Russell
text: The best Chili's Rellano in town hands down! Good Margarita's and nice servers. They have a nice Patio area and a Buffet on certain days. Good food Good atmosphere.

name: Jeremy Lennox
text: Decided to stop in for lunch because it’s the closest Mexican restaurant to our house. VERY glad we came in. Salsa is great, ingredients are fresh, staff is very friendly, and it’s an overall awesome atmosphere. Would recommend to anyone!

name: Kibbles n' Bits
text:
Honestly the worst meal I've had in a long time. They use the same sauce for everything. If you want authentic, go somewhere else, even Taco Bell is a better option.

No traditional Mexican "aguas". We asked what sauce the tamales have. The waiter answered "I don't know". Red? Green?? Not a single smile from any of the staff.

name: GOLDBULLIONTREASURES
text: I love their Authentic Mexican food. You have to go there and try it. Bring your family and friends. They have great prices and friendly staff.

name: Contessa Hudson
text: I have a wonderful experience every time I visit. Great service! Excellent food!

name: Kirk McCann
text: A good staple in the Mexican food options in Huntsville.  Good place for Margaritas during happy hour.  Though I dont recommend the high top Margaritas.  I do recommend the Taco Al Pastor.

name: danny newton
text: I believe this is the best Mexican restaurant in Huntsville Alabama. Our food was great. The service was excellent. I will be back!

name: Wanda Rice
text: Like the atmosphere! And good food!

name: Rose G
text: My family likes to eat here, a few times a month.  Foods good.  Everyone is friendly and helpful.

name: R. Spuhl
text: Good food, but the servers act almost disgusted that I'd interrupt their day...as if it's beneath their dignity to provide service.  After half a dozen visits with only one decent waiter/waitress I'm not going back.

name: Kecia Ross
text: Great food

name: Todd Needle
text: Great Mexican food. It can't beat

name: Adam B
text: Eat there during lunch. Food isn't bad, service can be slow but there is a buffet if in a time crunch

name: Sharon Nickoles
text: Great food. Great service.

name: Darrell Riley
text: Good lunch option if you are in the area.  In my opinion, better than the  other Mexican choices.  Buffet had plenty of choices and everything seemed fresh.

name: David Clark
text: Love their margaritas with sangria. Food is good too. Friendly wait staff

name: Jim Hennessy
text: really good food,  great staff, price is fair

name: Randall Elley
text: Great menu choices. Always good!!!

name: Michael Rushlow
text: Good food and good prices

name: Kyle Garrison
text: The food was amazing and filling. Service was friendly and quick

name: JaMese (Vlog Daddy)
text: Every time I go their, I always get more food than I can handle. Food tastes great. Friendly staff.

name: Stan D
text: There are much better Mexican restaurants in the area...unless you like your queso watered down.

name: Troy Scott
text: Always a great place to eat.  Nice friendly staff and excellent Mexican food

name: Bill Stratman
text: Good food all around and great margaritas.

name: Mary Blackwell
text: We go twice a week .  Love the staff, the food and the entire experience.  Everyone is just like family.  Highly recommend !

name: Jason Jenkins
text: Really good buffet especially the taco fixins.

name: Katy Gibson
text: Large guacamole can easy feed 5 people. And the beef chimichanga was delicious

name: Helen Harrand
text: Pretty dang good food and nice service.  Get the molcajete!  It's fabulous!

name: Matthew M.
text: Good food at good prices

name: Jarod Weckwerth
text: Food was delicious. Service was not the best. Took forever for our food to come out, and one of our guests burrito didn’t come out until were all almost finished.

name: Matt McLean
text: Very good food with quick service.

name: Scott Corbin
text: Great time at taco Tuesday!  Fantastic service!

name: Cecil Latta
text: Very good food service a little slow

name: Care Bear
text: Great food and friendly service!!. Not mentioned they have the BEST mixed drinks.

name: Amy Carroll
text: They have a nice place set up to eat outside. The food is great and the prices are fantastic

name: Haley Allen
text: Yummy, good service!

name: Vic R
text: I have visited a few times and each time I have had great food and great customer service.

name: Robbie Frost
text: Awesome salsa and chips!! Easy to get a seat.

name: Its me Jen again
text: Delicious food! Kids eat free on Mondays.

name: Tonya Woods
text: Good food drinks and atmosphere

name: A. Blanchard
text: Good food. Fun loud atmosphere.

name: Meka Philly
text: I believe this is the best Mexican food in North Alabama!

name: Lawrence Hess
text: Great lunch buffet, quick service at a great price.  Will definitely go again

name: Tim Nelson
text: Good service, food, and price. Will definitely be one our go to spots.

name: Joette Loveless
text: Best food and drinks, clean and great service

name: Stephen Langford
text: Set there at the bar for 15 minutes and no one ever took my order.  Don't think I will come back anytime soon. They took the orders of the parties around me, like wasn't even there.

name: A P
text: Food was ok. Large portions. Our particular waiter was the main reason I gave 3 stars. He was not friendly at all and kept us waiting to the point where we just went to register to pay and leave after he said he would be back to get our payment....He never came

name: Linda Latta
text: Good food, good drinks and good prices. We enjoy the outside eating area.

name: Will Bickett
text: The lunch buffet is the best deal in town.

name: joel rojas
text: Great food, good prices and fun environment at nights during weekends

name: Levi Macedo
text: Great food love the buffet  great customer service I will come again

name: Lauren Stevens
text: This place is great!! Especially for birthday's.... The salsa is really good

name: Kathleen Conaway
text: The food was good. You got enough food. The prices were good to.

name: Jonathan Pryor
text: The Taco Al Pastor is one of the best tacos I've ever had. Everything here is great, but this taco is exceptional.

name: Mikey Murphy
text: Friendly staff and delicious food! Get the El Omeca for a good presentation!

name: Renz Santos
text: A good experience for anyone feeling Mexican food. They host a fun trivia night every Wednesday.

name: Sy Belyeu Lankford
text: Good food! Waiter could have been more friendly, but otherwise good!

name: A P
text: Food was ok. Large portions. Our particular waiter was the main reason I gave 3 stars. He was not friendly at all and kept us waiting to the point where we just went to register to pay and leave after he said he would be back to get our payment....He never came

name: Will Bickett
text: The lunch buffet is the best deal in town.

name: Levi Macedo
text: Great food love the buffet  great customer service I will come again

name: Carl Schoenholz
text: The $7 weekday lunch buffet is one of the best deals for a good mexican lunch.

name: Sy Belyeu Lankford
text: Good food! Waiter could have been more friendly, but otherwise good!

name: Stephanie Watson-Barry
text: This is our favorite Mexican restaurant. We probably go at least weekly. It is always delicious.

name: Katrina Mejias
text: Saturday nights are Salsa night. Loved it!

name: Renz Santos
text: A good experience for anyone feeling Mexican food. They host a fun trivia night every Wednesday.

name: Robert Whiddon
text: Been here 4 times and the food had always been great

name: Veronica Johnson
text: Food was tasty,and plenty . Had leftovers

name: Will Howard
text: One of my favorite places for Mexican cuisine.

name: Corey Brown
text: I've always had a great meal here! I love their guacamole.

name: Preston Lively
text: I love this place. Their service and food is great. I usually get the tostada, chiles rellano and beans and rice. The chips and dip are always fresh. Also, food is always hot, not room temperature like other Mexican restaurants if tried.

name: Francisco Villarreal
text: It's always good and staff always friendly. Highly recommended!

name: Kathleen Carnell
text: Consistently great tasting food!

name: Michael Nelson
text: Good Mexican buffet for a quick lunch break.

name: Pete Shea
text: A bit pricier than a lot of Mexican, but always great food and service.

name: Scott Champion
text: They are great just like, the sister-like restaurants thats maybe why the have so many of them. Everthing is always so great. Sevice, food, and prices.

name: Mr. McPoop
text: If you're looking for taco al pastor in Huntsville, this is it!

name: Serena Graham
text: The food was bland and the beans was burnt.  Why they served, and charged me for that?

name: Edgar RODRIGUEZ
text: Good food great service

name: Carlos Matkins
text: The Veggie fajitas are 🔥🔥🔥

name: Peter Folgmann
text: El Omeca hits the spot when you want good mexican food and drinks.

name: Carl Esch
text: Good clean nice people.

name: Justin Howard
text: Great food but the inside does not impress.

name: DEEPoSEAN_
text: Excellent food and drinks. Reasonable price.

name: John Jumper
text: Clean, friendly and good food

name: Preston Taylor
text:
The food was absolutely amazing! I had a chimichanga and I usually go to Buenavista and pay $12.50 for a chimichanga and pay extra for everything. At this place it's only $7.99 and it comes with everything and it tastes so much better!!!
HIGHLY RECOMMEND.
GOOD BYE BUENEVISTA

name: leigh mccurry Fierro
text: Terrible steak seemed like they threw it  on the grill for a couple seconds  when it got to me it was still REFRIGERATOR COLD!!!  The service was OK they was mad that I complained about my steak I gave this place a one star rating just to wrote this review never go here I won't ever again

name: Angelo Contino
text: Awesome and friendly environment. Go there TODAY.

name: Damian “Yogi” Figures
text: I love the lunch buffet here! Can't get enough :-)

name: Elizabeth Henson
text: Clean, friendly and quick service, and best of all....amazing food!

name: K.Ross
text: Best Thursday night specials and the food is quick and delicious!

name: Debbie Dailey
text: Fresh and delicious. Large portions

name: Brandie Moore
text: Great food and great service!

name: Southern Reclaimed Salvage Barn
text: Great food and drinks! Great service as well!

name: Vi Vu
text: Oh my goodness! What a great find! Driving through Birmingham and decided to stop by. They have an extensive menu selection of all kinds of food offerings. We decided on the Botana de Camarones, which is a mix shrimp prepared 5 different ways. It was all good, although I especially liked the bacon wrapped shrimp and the butterflied fried shrimp the best. We also ordered a large portion of the guacamole...glad we did. It was chock full of avocado goodness - creamy just ripe avocados. Yum-My. We each ordered 3 tacos de tripas (no photo) and it was so good...just how I like them. A little crisp on the edges and chewy inside, a nice clean flavor. We will definately stop by when in the area. ☆☆☆☆☆

name: Aaron Gray
text: Good ambience and service, average food. We got the Tacos: Al pastor, Chorizo, Asada, Carnitas, and Pollo, as well as the Tamales Oaxaqueños. They were all okay. They didn't come with any tacos salsas, but we asked for some, and they brought out a couple in little dishes. The orange sauce had a bit of a sour off flavor and was too much vinegar for my taste, speaking as someone who does like vinegar based sauces. The brown salsa was better, with a smoky flavor. But honestly I didn't like any of their salsas that much, and preferred to eat the tacos with just salt. The Pastor was our favorite, with the Asada being our least favorite. The tamale also was just okay. I did really like the homemade tortillas though, and the ambience with the lights and music was spot on. And the staff were really friendly! So good points for those things.

name: Nicholas Blackstock
text:
My 3 fav Mexican restaurants/food trucks around town for some reason all begin with Taqueria! Coincidence or no?!

The place is small and somewhat tight honestly, but as Will has pointed out... the 2 or 3 times I've been here, it's never crowded, which is very strange! They definitely receive steady business, however. I love to order nachos at Mexi-Joints, even more traditional ones such as this place. The flavors are so amazing (chicken and beef)! Serving size to price ratios are perfect. Other menu items live up to high standards as well. I honestly don't have anything bad at all to say here...

If you're a Mexi-food lover, please do yourself a favor and give Taqueria a shot... I don't think you'll be disappointed at all!

name: Gottfried Kibelka
text:
Happy Mexican music,  cozy, slightly cramped dining room with plenty of  leather chairs, dark wood, and porch lights strung across the ceiling. All in all a pleasant, festive atmosphere. Fast, friendly service, a 1 L stein with  water, and a nice salsa with a big basket of chips made me feel welcome.
To my surprise: No vegetarian options on the menu (2018!). I asked the waitress if I could order the chile relleno as a vegetarian dish and she recommended queso fresco. I asked about lard and pork fat in the beans and she realized that they are not vegetarian and offered to double the rice instead. Queso fresco is not as fatty and gooey and was a recommendation I will use in the future.
The breading on the chile relleno was soft, not crisp as hoped for, but all in all tasted good. Pico de Gallo came in a small taco shell (cute) but was placed on top of iceberg salad reducing the amount of Pico de Gallo significantly. The rice was cooked perfectly and when mixed with the salsa that came with the chips, a really enjoyable side. I like my food spicy and was disappointed that there was no hot sauce on the table or fresh Jalapeno on the plate.
Still, I would have given 4 stars but $13 for a fried chile with rice felt a bit steep. The non-vegetarian lunch menu was priced much lower.

But if you want great food, good service, and a smile as you leave when you are done,
Then these guys/gals will make your day.

Now for the meal, it was very appealing to the nose upon arrival and my tongue was not disappointed. Very good food for all in my party.  Pricing was also very reasonable. text: After an already long day decided to satisfy that mexican craving for dinner. Big mistake. I'm visiting the area so got turned around trying to find it, no online menu so had to place order upon arrival. I can't tolerate spicy foods in any capacity so of course, seeing cheese sauce on a dish, I need to make sure. Asked for extra regular cheese instead of the spicy cheese sauce, but instead received skimpy cheese & a spicy beef & bean burrito. Really, after informing you of my severe intolerance to spicy food you didn't see the need to warn the beef &/or bean inside the burrito may be spicy?? I'm past starving so naturally I dive right in trusting my order is safe w/no spice. Total waste of time & money. Went to bed in pain & still hungry. What a horrible end to the day!!!

text:
Free been dip and salsa just for sitting down! This was sadly the highlight of the visit here.

When trying new Mexi-joints... i generally like to to go with a classic Nacho dish (Nachos Supremos in this case). Ehhh... Though not as large, a Nachos Bel Grande from Taco Bell would have been a bit tastier. The nacho dish was served on a large plate, and seemed a bit pre-pepared and popped in the oven... here's why I say that:

1. Food came out in about 5 minutes flat (if not less)
2. The plate itself and food on the bottom was hot along with singed edges on chips, while food on top was literally cold
3. Lettuce and veggies were not only cold, they were a bit wet as if rinsed right before refrigerating

So you agree? Pretty obvious right? Along with this, I like to eat my nachos with a fork... everything all mixed together. In this case, that's a good thing. If were to eat my nachos chip by chip, I'd be disappointed. Meat and chips on the bottom of the dish, and lettuce covering the entire top of the dish. In between these two layers were 3 separate "piles" of beans, cheese and sour creme. Really? Melted cheese only in 1 section of my NACHOS??? C'mon!

Service was great and decor is nice... nothing too fancy but feels like it should be a fun atmosphere... too bad the new chicken tacos at Taco Bell are a better experience!

text:
The service is always great and the food is always on point. I steer away from any American/Mexican choices at any similar restaurant. I go for the traditional/authentic choices if the restaurant offers them. I've been to the other local ones, and they don't. Here's what you need to look for; the conchinita, el pastor, and the steak tacos.
Want a local tip?**** Ask to have it Mexican style. It comes with corn or flour tortillas, lime wedges,  onion and cilantro topping, and an awesome habanero sauce with a ramekin of habanero relish****. Cant go wrong. Trust me.
The pork chops and the grilled chicken(not the half chicken but the marinated breast) are amazing. They also serve a grilled steak, tomato, and onion plate(get it Mexican style) that the flavor of a perfectly seasoned grilled steak just bursts through and marries with the onion and tomato.
I know this is hard to believe but even their rice is better than any others out there. It's not bland and red but it is ACTUALLY seasoned!
In the mood for a margarita? Don't bother with the regular margaritas but go straight for the Texas style. Made with fresh limes and tequila that will quench your thirst.
As you might be able to tell, I'm a regular to this place. The service is always great and my kids love to go anytime to get authentic Mexican. Last but not least, just about anytime I'm here there are always Mexican patrons. That is a good clue that these folks have good authentic food.

name: Aaron Gray
text: If you're a fan of tacos al pastor, and you dig spicy, this place is worth a look. Their jalapeño pico de gallo and habanero salsa gives them one of the hottest tacos in town. For me personally, I wish they had a little more flavor in addition to or instead of being so hot. But if heat's your thing, you might really like 'em.

name: Delima Bhagat
text: While my family has been going there to enjoy meals for about 5 years now, we've come to the decision that their bad service is definitely not worth our hard earned money. This is why:     {1} About a year ago, my brother, mom, and I ate there for dinner. We had a total of 3 orders of salsa, yet they decided to charge us for salsa because they said we had 7 among us 3, and only one per person is complementary. This was the first time they had ever mentioned this rule, and they neglected our proof that we had only 3, making us pay for something we didn't use. Also, they neglected to tell us this before writing our receipt.     {2} In a large coupon book we purchased, we found a coupon for a buy one get one free dinner plate for this place with the purchase of a drink (the requirement of getting a drink was in fine print). We went there with a group of 10 people, and we had 5 coupons. We decided to have 2 people per bill so that we could use the coupons. Unaware that water didn't count as a drink, the manager refused to allow us to use the coupons, even though we offered to get drinks or pay for drinks we didn't want to drink. After that, they told us that we couldn't use the coupon even if we did buy drinks because we were sitting at the same table even though we had separate checks, which wasn't a requirement listed on the coupon.     {3} My family is strictly vegetarian. On Wednesday nights, they have a buy one entree get another free deal with certain restrictions. Because none of the options were solely vegetarian, my mother and I had replaced a beef burrito with one with vegetables inside for a $0.75 charge for the substitution. This is what we had done for years now, yet today they refused to allow for this change. Apparently, these changes wouldn't be allowed because "it's too similar to a dish [Vegetarian Burrito] that's not included in the deal." We offered to pay as much as it would cost to buy a Vegetarian Burrito, yet they still refused. We even talked to  manager who knows us pretty well for going there over the years and told him how this is what we've done for years, yet he told us that to his knowledge, they weren't allowed to do that in the first place. Literally sounded like he was making up some random stories.          ~So as you can tell, this place neglected the fact that we were usual customers and treated us poorly, making up false regulations with no explanation and trying to overcharge us. We seemed to overlook 1 and 2 because the food was worth it, but there comes a point where their bad service reflects on the goodness of their food. Plus, what's a decent meal without good service no matter how the food tastes? Isn't the customer always right? Not at Amigo's! So do yourself a favor: save your money. Going to Taco Bell is even better than wasting your time here.~

name: Mathew Riva
text:
What a gem. Walking in and taking in the joys of the not just the classic and fun ambiance that is sure to be a.....smile to your face, but the humorous karaoke going on will sure leave you with memories to share!

Party of three came in for just some margaritas and they came out pretty strong and sweet. Margs seemed a little higher priced than expected but the laughter we were able to share was worth the time and money.

We sat at the bar and then realized it wasn’t “the” bar. There was a cooler in front of us that had beer in it but the margs were made at the other half of the restaurant in the “real” bar. If you see it, you’ll understand, I hope.

The chandeliers and lighting...can’t beat it. Just go, smile, have some drinks and enjoy your life.

name: Cdubs
text:
I wanted to give this restaurant the benefit of the doubt, since it is fairly new, but 4 out of the 5 times we have eaten here it has been a bad experience. Two experiences that come to mind:

1) My wife and I waited for over an hour for food that normally takes 10-15 minutes to cook. We reminded the waitress multiple times that we had ordered and still took forever. Meanwhile we watched 3 or 4 tables come in, eat, and leave. When we finally received our food, it was wrong.

2)We hadn't eaten here for a couple weeks given the experience listed above, but yet again we decided to give this place the benefit of the doubt. But instead of going and eating inside, we ordered it to go. I repeated myself to the hostess on the phone about the way that i wanted my food, so right away i had a sneaking suspicion that i needed to check my food before i left. Of course when i arrived the food was wrong, so she apologized and took the food back to "remake" it. Twenty seconds later she comes back with my food, and i knew it was too quick to "remake" it. When i arrived home i saw that all she did was pick some of the stuff out and throw it back in the old tortillas.

Unfortunately there is not many Mexican restaurants in the area to choose from, so we got to make do. But this is for the passerby's and the visitors who come through the area. Food is ok, but doesn't make up for the god awful service.

name: Chris Powers
text:
While visiting Eufaula for the first time, we had no less than 3 people tell us to eat at El Jalisco for a great meal.
We arrived at 3pm and we were seated immediately. Our waitress Debbie showed up and took our drink order pretty quick. The medium top shelf Margaritas she brought us were enormous and delicious! See photos...
Once we got our drinks however, it took a very long time to see the waitress again for our actual food order to be taken.
I ordered a combo of chili relleno/ beef taco  with rice and refried beans.
The food was okay, but not great. Not the usual spice pizazz I am used to from traditional Mexican fare.
I got a spice kick from the salsa that came with the chips though.
My overall feeling is that we spent too much for the meal, but Debbie was delightful and accommodating and made a killer margarita.
I will probably return one day when in the area, but stick to the lunch specials which are cheaper but not as flexible in choice selection.

resp.text: Chris, thanks for trying us out while you were in town! We want to provide our customers with entrées and services that's just as great as our margaritas, so we'll be sure to pass along your feedback to our team. We look forward to welcoming you back for a five-star visit the next time you're in the area. -Yadira, Owner

name: Emma Gannaway
text: Terrible service. Terrible taste. We were barely greeted as we entered the door. After we were seated and our order was taken and given to us, we never saw the waitress until we asked for our check. Our food had no flavor, except for the Buffalo wings on the appetizer menu. We weren’t even given well wishes on our way out. Save your time and money and visit the pizza shop across the street.

resp.text: Emma, when you visit our restaurant, you should expect to be met with warm and welcoming service the moment you walk through our door, so we're very sorry to hear that we missed the mark. We're looking into this to make sure that our staff is providing our customers with an excellent experience throughout their whole visit. We'd love another chance to help you find something on our menu that you'll truly enjoy. -Yadira, Owner

name: Mike Canady
text: While visiting this beautiful small town we tried Mexican restaurant. The atmosphere was pleasant. Our server Amber was great. The food was good.

resp.text: Mike, thanks for stopping by during your visit to Eufaula! There's more to a great meal than just good food, which is why we're proud to offer a welcoming atmosphere and excellent service as well. We hope to serve you more of our delicious Mexican dishes the next time you're in town. -Yadira, Owner

name: Martin Burrow
text:
Good food and very reasonably priced. Standard selection of menu items, with a nice atmosphere.

Parking is a little bit of a challenge, but that's with everything on the street. It's a nice walk to the restaurant, so find your best spot and enjoy the walk.

resp.text: Martin, serving delicious Mexican dishes at an affordable price is something we're proud to do! Our central location comes with challenges, but walking to our restaurant from your parking spot is a great way to see the Eufaula. Looking forward to welcoming you back in the future! -Yadira, Owner

name: Mucaco007
text: Im a traveler 🧳 from Georgia I stop with my family by this restaurant, food and customer service excellent! Margaritas very good.

resp.text: Thank you for stopping by while you were in town! We're proud to provide our customers with delicious Mexican dishes and excellent service. We hope to serve you more margaritas in the future! -Yadira, Owner

name: Gerry Whitaker
text: One of the last remaining excellent places to eat in Eufaula. You will find a pleasant atmosphere and staff are pleasing and attractive.  The food is excellent and helpings are huge. I recommend this as the place for your eating experience 👌.

resp.text: Gerry, serving up big portions of delicious dishes is our specialty! A great atmosphere and friendly service is what turns a good meal into a great one, so that's what you can always count on when you dine with us. We look forward to welcoming you back in the future! -Yadira, Owner

name: The Biddle Boys
text: If I could give zero stars I would. First time there with family and will not return or recommend. My husband asked for no sour cream got some on his plate and a side of it, my sister in law ordered the fajita chicken nachos apparently the veggies are .99 extra, and they charge for chips and salsa at their own discretion. The waitress checked on us once, I had to flag down another waitress for water refills for the whole table. When we got our bills we noticed the extra charge for the veggies and 15% tip was already added. Asked about this and told too bad nothing can be done. Asked to talk to the manager, another waitress came to talk to us and said not our problem. Finally got the manger to have her tell us that she doesn't know why the other waitress came to talk to us even though that waitress said the manager sent her. Explained that when you look at the menu it says fajita chicken nachos and not that it's just the chicken and veggies are extra, she admitted the menu has mistakes and is hard to read but too bad because we're not a regular customer who understands that you'll be charged for stuff at the restaurants discretion. Customer service definitely needs to be retrained as all we were told is oh well pay your bill we don't care that you had a bad experience, that the waitress ignored the table or that she will argue with you when you say something was wrong. Would not recommend if it was the last place to eat.

resp.text: I want to assure you that our customers' satisfaction is always our top priority here. I'm very sorry for the confusion during your visit. I am looking into this situation further to ensure that our staff is consistently attentive and communicating our policies clearly. If you would like to discuss your concerns with me any further, please don't hesitate to reach out offline. -Yadira, Owner

name: Cherie Taylor

name: Jessica Skiles
text: Please READ THE MENU!!! Ordering the chicken Fajita Nachos you will not get the onions and bell peppers on the nachos it is meat cheese and chips...if asked do you want the veggies it is because you will be charged extra for them. Regardless of the service you get if you have a party over 6 you WILL be charged 15% gratuities...you can be charged for extra for chips or salsa at their discretion...if you order cheese dip ASK for the chips that are meant to go with the cheese dip or you will not get those....I am sure it is dependent on the waitress you get but if you need more to drink you must ask for that also...if you happen to have an issue with the food or service do not expect to talk to a manager until you have talked to multiple waitresses and again request management before you eat your food but know she can not change anything on your ticket because the owner will say it is on the menu and the same manager will tell you the menu has mistakes on it and can be confusing...This is your every day Mexican joint the food was typical american mexican food but the service is not the kind and understanding typical restaurant service...eat at your own discretion but check you bill!!!!

resp.text: Jessica, when you raise an issue to our staff, you should expect to receive helpful service in return. I am very sorry for the confusion during your visit. resp.text: I'm glad you had a chance to stop in and give us a try on your way to the beach, Karen. The team and I look forward to continuing to impress you on future visits. -Yadira, Owner

text: Steak fajitas were great margarita was good

text: Food was great!!!!! They would not give my wife a menu. They only allow one menu per table and the one they gave us was dirty and full of salsa. Very frustrating!!!! They gave no explanation as to why.

name: ChaCha Fance (Mrs. Fance)
text: I've been here multiple times. It's the best Mexican food place in Eufaula. However, there's often a wait to be seated and on top of that, table service is slow..... The delicious food always makes up for the slow service, though.

resp.text: We're so glad you enjoyed stopping by, Charnita! We'd love to see you here again. -Yadira, Owner

name: Jason Pizza

text: Sometimes there's a bit of a language barrier but the food is excellent

We appreciate your patience regarding some of our staff's English, but we can assure you that our entire team is committed to making sure that you have a great visit. We'd love another chance to provide you with a five-star experience. -Yadira, Owner

resp.text: Ron, thank you for taking a moment to show your support! Looking forward to seeing you back our way again. -Yadira, Owner

text:
I came

for the tacos and left full and happy. Great service, great prices and great staff. Much better than Old Mexico.

text: Food was good. Very quick service.  Everything, including the restrooms were clean .

name: Ty Brummitt
text: This is the better of the two Mexican restaurants in Eufaula, and the customer volume is proof of that. They offer an all you can eat option on Sunday which is what I ordered. The food is delivered fast, hot, and it is delicious. This place offers to go orders as well. The staff is very friendly, and the prices aren't high. I highly recommend this place to anyone in the area wanting a good Mexican lunch or dinner. You won't regret it.

resp.text: Thanks so much for recommending us, Ty! We're honored to be your favorite local spot for Mexican food, and we really appreciate your support. Hope we get to welcome you back soon! -Yadira, Owner

name: Cindy Schicho
text: Great little stopover from Atlanta to Panama City Beach.right off 431. Friendly town, good variety on menu. We ordered to take out and eat at the table on the wide sidewalk. Very quick and food was delicious.

name: Debra Clemons
text: Foods great,service was alright but it was busy

name: genesis deras
text: Always goes above and beyond with food taste and delivery!😋 Love the fried ice cream and they have one of the best servers Oscar 😉

name: Dr. Jeffery Reed
text: Moldy much!? We were seated and right away greeted by a server. While waiting on our drinks, well noticed the black mold. Had we wouldn’t have looked up to see where the ac vents were because it was blowing right on us. We would have not seen it at all. But there it was seeping  out the vents and growing on the side. You see where someone tried cleaning it. Just nasty! We got up and walked out. Took our business down the street. We won’t be back when coming to Eufaula. I also have photos but cannot figure how to upload them. Old age and new technology.

text: The food was good, but the service was slow. My husband and I called in our order for pick-up & we still had to wait for our food after we got there. resp.text: We apologize that your order took a bit longer than you expected, Megan, but it's great you enjoyed your meal. We regret that you didn't get any chips and salsa this time, and we're happy to make sure you get those the next time you come pick up an order. Hope to serve you again soon. -Yadira, Owner

resp.text: Glad we could get you taken care of as quickly as possible, Clifford! Thank you for joining us, and we look forward to you coming back. -Yadira, Owner

text: A little slow with service but excellent food and atmosphere.

name: Kim Miller
text: I'm from California and know Mexican food! And now I've finally found a restaurant here in the south that actually knows how to cook it! Who knew that in Eufaula, one would find authentic Mexican food! The first time I visited El Jalisco I had their carnitas....so good! This time I had their chicken mole...pronounced mo-lay. It was fantastic! I don't know of any other restaurant for 50 miles that serves chicken mole. The food is great, the service is good, the prices are very reasonable & they make a mean margarita! I will be stopping by every chance I get!!

resp.text: We'll keep making carnitas, mole, and margaritas, Kim, as long as you keep coming back to enjoy them. Loving that you've had such a great time with each visit. We're looking forward to welcoming you back again soon. See you then! -Yadira, Owner

text: Great food, excellent service and fast. It's a little tight, not much room to move around but still is 5 star. Highly recommended.

text:
Good food, lots of it, with fast and friendly service.
The guacamole was delicious and the beer was ice cold, with a chilled mug and lime.

We would like to come back and try some of their other items on the menu. See ya again!!

name: Kyann Stringer
text: Waited an hour and 30 minutes on our food. Waitres has our daughter change her order due to kids eat free tonight, said 12 and under eat free off kids menu. Waiters said new cook burnt the chemichonga. Manager said " only 2 cook. Dont know bout burn but I make right" . We had to get other servers to refill our drinks. Food was delivered 1.5 hr after we were seated. Bill was delivered and charged for child meal. Went to manager and was informed 10 and under and he knew waitres told us 12 and had her change her order. I explained that server should have come back to our table and told us...manager replied that he did not care. We were charged for extra chips that we only asked for after 1 hr of waiting. My husband told manager we would not be back, he stated he did not care it was up to us and people who say they wont be back do show back up. name: Beth Wright
text:
This was a great find!  Many restaurants in Fort Payne are closed on Sunday and I was struggling to find a place I wanted to go. There were multiple Mexican restaurants open but I didn't want a heavy greasy meal topped with a slab of cheese, so I was delighted to see other items on Mi Ranchito's menu.

I'm not a big fan of TexMex food as my brother lives in Dallas and I've had plenty of real Mexican food, which I vastly prefer. At Mi Ranchito, I had several authentic Mexican taco fillings I'd never had before on housemade corn tortillas — and with only a scattering of cotija cheese on one of them. The food was absolutely delicious and my server was a nice young man with whom I enjoyed speaking. When I asked to take the freshly made chips and salsa with me, he offered me some salsa verde to take back to where I was staying, too.

For those of you who are fans of Tex-Mex food, they have plenty of that, too, things like burritos and chimichangas, etc. I bet they're equally delicious.

And my whole meal, which consisted of one taco and one doblado (a double- sized taco, something new to me), unbelievably cost less than $6 excluding the generous tip I left! I highly recommend Mi Ranchito.

name: Rhonda Pascual
text:
I liked it,because it Is more like the type of food from Central America. It had Vegan options and that's a plus for me,as I cannot eat meat due to a vitamin deficiency. The vegan meal I tried ( enchiladas) was very good and I was given the option of regular enchilada sauce or salsa verde. I chose salsa verde and it was awesome! My husband got the carne asada and he loved it. A plus is that their tortillas are handmade and not full of those stinky chemicals that most store bought tortillas have.
I liked their chips,but I don't think everyone would,if they aren't accustomed to traditional Central American food. They use tortillas( handmade) ,cut them up and make chips from them,so they are thicker and crunchier. They have two sauces that are given with them. One is salsa verde( my favorite) and a tomato based homemade sauce. This restaurant hasn't been open long and it is still being decorated. The place is a Mom and Pop place and has a family type,friendly atmosphere. They do take both cash and debit/ credit cards. I will tell you that they have the absolute best Pico De Gallo in the area and I have tried them all.( They put lemon juice in their's.)  My two grown kids liked Mi Ranchito  too. We will definitely be back!

text:
We went on a Thurs night and it wasn’t crowded. Our waiter was very friendly and attentive, and we found him to be courteous about social distancing/mask wearing. We sat outdoors and it was comfortable and sheltered despite the wind and rain.

We ordered off the vegetarian menu and our meals arrived quickly, and they were fresh and delicious. Very affordable and generous portion sizes. They also have a good kids menu, so we all felt catered to :)

We’re from out of town but we’ll definitely return here next time we’re in Montgomery, and we would recommend this restaurant to others!

text:
This was rough.

Let's start with the positives:
The food was good and in enough quantities.
There was a handful of vegan and vegetatian options.

And that's about it

Now, the negatives:
The antimasker waiter that others are complaining about was our waiter. He took his mask off several times and told us that we didn't need to worry about the virus and that we should dine inside.

He over shared constantly.

He swore at us regularly.

He invaded our space without his mask on several times.

We will not be coming here again and recommend that no one else go as well.

If you're interested in responsibly helping to prevent a deadly and infectious disease, please don't dine here.

text:
SIGNIFICANT LACK OF PROPER SANITATION!
BE SAFE, STAY AWAY!

Manager sat us down at a table without wearing a mask, and when requested to wear a mask stated "if Trump isn't going to wear a mask, then I'm not going to."

This is absolutely unacceptable and outrageous that the manager yells at potential customers, who work in the healthcare field and want to save their patients from possible COVID-19 infection, for them politely requesting that he wears his mask. Would score less than one star if possible.

text:
Extensive menu of good Mexican food in a restaurant with TVs. It gets noisy with a crowd but the green enchiladas were good--and that's how you measure a Mexican restaurant!

My wife's Margarita was good and so were the chips.

The service was quick too at a busy time, too.

name: Chris Harden
text: I've tried several places in Montgomery and Selma, during my stay here, and I can honestly say, I've FINALLY found a place worth my time & money. I had the carne azada, my girlfriend had the fish tacos. Both were delicious. We were both very hungry and left extremely full, with food leftover. The medium sized beer was huge. I must say, I will definitely be back. Nice to FINALLY find a place to dine here.

name: Robert Patrick McMahon
text: Typical Americanized "Mexican Food."  Don't expect to recreate that trip to Cancun but the food is consistent and good.

Priced very reasonable. Restaurant appeared very clean and the little waitress( employees daughter) was adorable and super sweet and did a excellent job. We will eat here again.

text: Food is great. Food comes quick. Just service isn't the best best.

He was rude and gave me a rude stare like I was the problem.  I was going to order a new meal but the service was not worth it! The server never came back to the table, she decided to go make drinks at the bar!!! Worse service I'll never return!!!! The Jalapenos in Pepper tree is much better friendly and great service! Don't waste your time here!! If I could give no stars i would!

Horrible. The jalapeño poppers- they were burnt and tasted terrible. Had enchiladas for the entree, they resembled what one would get in a TV dinner, and they don’t even serve them with rice and beans, only a few pieces of lettuce. Easily the worst tasting Mexican food I have ever eaten. I asked waiter about the lack of rice and beans and he was just surly, saying that I should have read the menu better (I was prepared to buy rice and beans in hopes that they had some taste, but he never gave me the chance).

The stomach cramps began within ten minutes of leaving this restaurant and now I’m confined to my hotel bathroom for the remainder of the evening.

Steer clear.

This is a travesty of telenovela proportions in my opinion!!! Their sangria-sabotage is served straight from the bottle - presumably the storebought brand bottle they serve. After collecting my jaw off the floor, I ordered sweet tea with lemon...livin' NOTSOMUCH la vida loca.

Unfortunately,  we will not be back due to poor quality food. The place is cute but floors were very dirty for being newly reopened.  I truly wish they had fresh and authentic Mexican food.  Sad day.

name: Ryan McCullough
text: Great authentic Mexican food. The Mexican style chorizo taco is one of the best I've ever had. Flauta was amazing covered in cheese sauce topped w/ guacamole. The tamale covered in chile con carne was rich and delicious. I also asked for spicy and they served a housemade spicy green sauce that was amazing. Staff was very friendly and it was extremely clean and well put together.

name: Debi Jackson
text: We had a little wait but we felt sure it was because they were short staffed. Aren't all businesses at this time? They were trying their best to keep everything running smoothly and were doing a great job. The service was excellent and the food was well worth the wait. We highly recommend.

name: Jessica Pinon
text: We've visited here several times and for this area, the food and service were great! If you like really spicy-hot salsa, ask for the salsa verde. I had them put that on my enchiladas instead of cheese, and it was so hot! It was made fresh, and really is spicy. The staff is always friendly, and we always get fresh hot chips when we arrive. If you haven't tried it yet, make it out for dinner sometime.

name: Teresa McCann

text: Man if you haven't tried this place out. You are truly missing out. They maybe small,but the food alone is worth being in there. Go try for yourself.

text: Just got pick up but they were so fast and oh my Lord delicious. Our cashier was not only very patient but so sweet even though they were super busy. Definitely a date night spot!

text: Lovely outside seating over looking Opelika and East University. Excellent Mexican cuisine.

name: Patrick Williams
text: Our family went and had a mostly wonderful meal - it was certainly the most authentic we have seen in Auburn so far. The Carnitas plate and the sopes were incredibly good - I will crave the sopes!! We will order those again and again. The drinks were average - the margs and fruit punch were a tad too sweet for us. Wife had a burrito of the day: it was cheap but would not do it again - was almost all filler of rice and tortilla. Salsa bar was excellent - something for everyone on the bar. They were so close to a five star, but just a few too many misses.

name: Shena Moran
text: This restaurant has recently changed owners and is now awful! The cheese dip was weirdly chunky. The beans tasted sour and appeared to have been microwaved. Our order (4 people) came out and was incorrect. It took forever for lunch, 1 1/2 hours total.  I kept two of the tacos that came out that we didn’t order b/c I had already opened them up and touched them. Our waiter left them at the table and we were hungry from waiting forever, so we shared them while waiting for our correct order(which took another 15 mins). We were charged for the tacos that we didn’t order and upon asking the manager to take those off of our bill he was rude and refused! I told him that we would not be back because of terrible customer service and the food wasn’t good. He didn’t seem to care. Oh well, the food and customer service under the previous owners was good, don’t expect that now.

To top it off the entire time we are waiting there was a group of four females in the table beside us on the phone cursing real loud, jumping up dancing and acting a fool. My wife decided to go check on the waitress and she was sitting up front on her phone. Needless to say we left and probably won’t go back. Very unprofessional establishment.

Lol I heard everyone had came for the margarita tower so maybe they weren’t ready for that volume but my friend had came on another day earlier in the daytime and loved it. So, I definitely would try again on a day that may not be so packed. I believe on a more relaxed day that the food could be better as well as the service.

The chips were all broken up and the salsa had good taste but was mostly liquid. Maybe in a yr I will try it again, but not anytime soon.

text:
Going to give them another chance, of course...please don’t let me down Taco Bell!
I saw a whole bunch of 5/4 ⭐️ recent reviews and Inhope they are accurate and not just to bring their online rating up...we shall see...I will update after my visit.

You know for a long time I prayed for a Taco Bell to come to Randolph County.  Now we
have one, it has just continued to go downhill no matter how many times I give the Roanoke Taco Bell another chance!!  This time, like every one of the last three times I visited, the order was messed up!   This time I got what I ordered by name, but three little pieces of steak on the steak nachos and less than a half container of LIMP nacho fries and a reheated taco salad does NOT make a decent meal.  And yes, the line was moving like a snail...I thought maybe it was the guy up ahead ordering, but I am tired of making excuses for this Taco Bell!!!  Other Taco Bells don't have such crappy service and food!   Management,  if you are worth anything, figure out "who" the problems are and correct/fire them.  Here's a pic of the order of nacho fries, you be the judge...
Ps.  I'm the one that gave you a 4 Star rating right after you opened...smh.

Slower than the first time, and the restaurant was in bad need of some janitorial services. Trash all over the floor, tables that needed wiping down, and the staff was seemingly unconcerned with it. Definitely will not recommend this store until management has dealt with the problems.

name: Gabriel Mendez-Frances
text:
I've been here about five times now and can without a doubt say that they are my favorite Mexican restaurant in Tarrant.

Their main specialty is tacos, obviously, but they also offer a good selection of specialty plates including pork chops, steak, soups, shrimp, and more. I've been trying out their different styles of taco and would recommend tacos al pastor.

Service was fast and attentive, due in part to it being such a small spot. I kind of prefer cozy eateries like this though, would definitely recommend checking it out if you're local or just passing by.

I could eat mexican cuisine 3 meals a day, year round!! I've eaten at nearly EVERY Mexican restaurant in Birmingham, & ALWAYS try every Taco Truck, I pass. This was hands down the best refried beans & freshest, best tasting cilantro, I've EVER eaten, as if straight from the garden! Those beans were delicious, obviously homemade!
